title: salmon ball
directions: Mix all together and shape into a ball.
Chill 1/2 hour.
Roll ball in nuts and parsley.
"This recipe is good served on Triscuits crackers.
Serves 8 but sometimes I use 3 to 4 packages of cream cheese to stretch the recipe."

title: lemon cheese bars(makes 24 to 36 bars)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix dry cake mix, 1 egg and 1/3 cup oil until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup of these crumbs for topping.
Pat the crumbly mixture in an ungreased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Beat cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice and 1 egg until light and smooth.
Spread over the baked crumb mixture by spooning it.
Sprinkle with 1 cup of crumbs.
Bake 15 minutes.
Cool.
Cut in bars.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in oil in saucepan.
Combine soups, taco sauce and green chilies and heat.
Combine with the meat mixture. In casserole, place a layer of tostados, a layer of meat mixture and a layer of cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: golden punch
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
May be mixed ahead of time.
Add the ginger ale and pineapple sherbet when ready to serve.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Thaw dough.
Cut in half.
Press dough out; place cheese on dough the length of bread.
Add pepperoni the length of bread. Start rolling dough on sides away from you, forming a tight loaf. Place seam on bottom.
Brush top with beaten egg yellow.
Score top of bread with thin slice.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients and add.
Cool to lukewarm, then add yeast dissolved in warm water.
Mix in about 8 1/2 cups flour to cake batter consistency.
Let rise, uncovered, until double.
Punch down.
Add about 2 cups flour, baking powder and soda.
Mix and then cover and let rise two hours until double. Punch down.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: carrot salad
directions: Grate the carrots and pour the lemon juice over them.
Mix well.
Stir in the mayonnaise and salt.
Chill for several hours. Garnish with parsley before serving.

title: chocolate-filled caramel buns
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 9-inch square pan or 9-inch round cake pan.
Spread frosting over bottom of pan; press pecans into frosting.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Cut all vegetables into bite-sized pieces.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix with the vegetables.
Cover and chill for at least 12 hours.
Stir occasionally.
It will last the whole day without refrigerating.
Good for you.
Not very fattening.
A robust flavor the men will enjoy.

title: microwave chocolate fudge
directions: Mix ingredients in bowl until blended.
Top with 1 stick butter (unmelted).
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir until smooth.
Blend in 1 cup chopped pecans.
Pour into wax lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill.

title: cannoli
directions: Combine Ricotta cheese, whipping cream, powdered sugar and vanilla in blender until mixture is quite thick.
Fold in coarsely chopped chocolate and citron.
Stuff into cannoli shells shortly before serving.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and decorate with half a candied cherry at either end, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pumpkin souffle crunch
directions: Combine pumpkin and sugar, mixing thoroughly. Add milk, egg and melted margarine. Stir; add remaining ingredients and pour into a greased casserole dish. Cover with Crunch Topping (see following recipe) and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: butter brickle and peach dessert
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour peaches and juice in pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix over top.
Melt butter and pour over top. Sprinkle coconut over top, then add pecans.
Bake at 350° (325° for glass pan) for 1 hour.

title: frozen corn
directions: Mix all together in large roaster pan.	Bake at 350° for one hour, stirring occasionally.
Cool and freeze in containers or freezer bags.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix butter and shortening until creamy.
Add sugar and eggs. Blend in flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Shape dough into balls.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; roll balls in mixture.
Place on an ungreased sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Stir together dressing mix, sour cream, and mayonnaise. Combine tomatoes, onions and peppers. In a large salad bowl, crumble half the cornbread, top with half tomato mixture, 1/2 cheese, 1/2 corn and beans and half of the dressing mixture. Repeat layers. Chill 3 hours.

title: olive-cheese ball
directions: Mix cheese and flour; mix in butter or margarine.
Mold 1 teaspoon dough around each olive (work dough with hands if it seems dry).
Shape into ball; place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Heat oven to 400° and bake until set, 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen. Do not use self-rising flour.

title: molasses crispies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg.
Add molasses.
Blend dry ingredients together; add to creamed mixture.
Chill dough.
Dip by spoonfuls.
Roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugars.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Let stand overnight.
Wash off and drain.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes, then pour into jars and seal.

title: muffins in a pitcher
directions: Pour boiling water on Bran Buds or 100% Bran.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
Add buttermilk and bran mixture.
Add flour that was sifted with baking soda and salt.
Add All-Bran. Mix until ingredients are moistened.
Store in covered container. Will keep about 3 weeks.
To cook, put in muffin tins (greased) and bake at 400° for 12 to 20 minutes.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Cream eggs, butter and sugar.
Add milk and undrained pineapple.
Fold in bread cubes.
Pour in casserole dish.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine sugar and oil; add beaten eggs and mix well.
Add other ingredients, adding apples and coconut last.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: greek chicken
directions: Wash chicken (remove skin if desired).
Cut 1 lemon in half. Squeeze juice of lemon over chicken in broiler pan.
Sprinkle fresh oregano, basil, garlic powder, salt and pepper over lemon coated chicken.
Broil until light brown; remove from broiler and turn chicken over, swishing both sides of chicken in the juice.
Cut second lemon and squeeze over uncooked side and season with seasonings.
Broil until brown.
Baste while cooking with juice from pan.
Place cooked chicken over cooked rice (prepared as box directs).
Spoon chicken bastings over chicken and over rice. Garnish with fresh parsley and quartered tomato.
Enjoy.

title: grilled baked beans
directions: Fry bacon until crispy.
Add onions and peppers and cook until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Stir in sugar, barbecue sauce and syrups.
Put the beans in a 12 x 6 x 3-inch foil pan.
Add bacon mixture, beer or apple juice and brisket ends.
Stir to mix. To grill, set the pan on the grill over hot coals.
Cover grill and, stirring three times, cook 40 to 60 minutes, depending on the amount of liquid desired.
To cook indoors, heat oven to 400°, assemble as directed, cover pan with loose foil tent and bake 40 to 60 minutes, stirring three times.
Makes 6 cups.

title: easy party punch
directions: Combine ingredients in given order.
Add ice.
Yields 57 servings.

title: frozen baked potatoes
directions: Scrub the baking potatoes; bake at 425° until tender, 50 to 60 minutes.
With electric mixer, blend together the milk, sour cream sauce mix, salt, cumin seed and pepper.
Let stand 10 minutes. Cut thin, lengthwise slice from each potato; discard.
Scoop out centers.
Add to sauce mixture with 2 tablespoons butter.
Beat until fluffy.
Add more milk, if needed.
Spoon into potato shells; sprinkle with paprika.
Freeze, covered, for up to 2 weeks.

title: chewy choc-cookies
directions: Mix and drop onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 40 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together the sugar and shortening. Then add the 6 eggs (1 or 2 at a time), beating entire time. Blend in the flour, flavorings and salt. Cook in a well-greased and floured tube pan. Spoon the mixture into the pan; don't pour. Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean. Do not overbake.

title: cheese cake
directions: Melt butter.
Mix in graham crackers and spread on bottom of spring-form type pan.
Separate egg whites and yolks.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Set aside.
Beat egg yolks until they begin to thicken.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add sour cream, cream cheese, lemon and vanilla.
Beat until completely mixed.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour in spring-form pan and bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Turn off oven but leave cake in for another hour.
Remove from oven and let it sit out for another hour.
Refrigerate for a couple of hours before eating.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Use own judgment if more milk is needed when you mix corn.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until it is custard-like all through.

title: broiled mackerel
directions: Cut fish into serving pieces; arrange in shallow ovenproof dish.
Combine olive oil, lemon juice, parsley, basil, cheese and garlic in bowl; mix well.
Pour over fish.
Marinate for 1 hour, turning several times; drain.
Broil for 5 to 7 minutes or until fish flakes easily.
May grill 4 to 6 inches from coals for 5 to 7 minutes on each side, if preferred.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: pasta house salad
directions: Mix the first five ingredients in large salad bowl.
Blend oil and red wine vinegar in blender.
Add salt and pepper; blend well. Add Parmesan.
Pour over lettuce; toss.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars together.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Stir into creamed mixture. Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased baking sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 10 minutes.
Can add 1 cup cut up gumdrops along with coconut or leave coconut out all together.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Boil 1 cup water.
Pour over shortening, sugar and salt. Blend and let cool.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add to first mixture after it has cooled.
Add beaten eggs.
Stir in flour, one cup at a time.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight.

title: chunky chocolate bars
directions: Prepare and bake brownie mix as directed on box using cake like directions.

title: spaghetti for fifty people
directions: Cook meat, onions and bell peppers in enormous pot until meat is cooked.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, salt, sugar and cayenne pepper.

Cook for at least 1 1/2 hours or longer if you want your area to smell good. Cook spaghetti according to package directions. Combine sauce with drained spaghetti, or top spaghetti with sauce. Serves 50.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Add in order listed, adding eggs one at a time.
Bake in pie shell about 40 minutes at 350°.

title: no name casserole
directions: Brown sausages; add onions and celery.
Add sugar, chili powder and soup; simmer awhile and then drain all beans and add to sausage mixture.
Let simmer for a long time, maybe 2 to 4 hours. Serve over rice.

title: slaw
directions: Grind the cabbage, celery, carrots, onion and tomatoes. Set aside.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place cooked chicken that has been deboned in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 3 cups of broth and 1 can cream of chicken soup; pour over chicken.
Mix flour, margarine, black pepper and enough buttermilk to make a thin batter; pour over chicken.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: baity's party punch
directions: In a large container (5 gallon minimum), Mix Kool-Aid, ginger ale and punch.
Stir in water. Add lemon juice and sugar to taste, stirring well. Add ice cubes before serving.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook and drain spinach well.
Beat egg yolks; mash cream cheese and add to hot soup.
Add spinach, beaten egg whites and Parmesan cheese.
Put in casserole dish; top with cheese or French fried onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: classic candied sweet potatoes
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until tender; drain.
Peel and cut potatoes lengthwise into 1/2-inch slices.
Melt butter and sugar over medium heat.
Add lemon rind and ginger.
Put potatoes in a shallow, well buttered baking pan. Pour butter-sugar mixture on top.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes, or until glazed.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: venita's enchiladas
directions: Brown meat, onion, seasoning package, garlic powder and chili powder all together; drain and set aside.
Mix together enchilada sauce, mushroom soup and tomato soup.
Heat on low fire; simmer and stir with wire whisk.
Put 2 to 3 tablespoons sauce in bottom of pan; dip tortillas in sauce, then add meat and cheese, then roll and lay in pan.
Add green chilies and extra cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: special peach pudding
directions: Cover peaches with 1 cup sugar; set aside.
Combine remaining sugar with remaining ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Fold in peaches.
Pour into well-greased deep baking dish.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Serve hot or cold with whipped cream.

title: carrot salad
directions: Steam carrots and cauliflower about 5 minutes and set aside.

title: eat it raw apple bread
directions: Cream butter; add the sugar slowly.
Beat until light in color.
Beat in eggs.
Mix flour, salt, soda and baking powder; add to mixture.
Add milk, apples, nuts and vanilla.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil, water, pumpkin, nuts and raisins.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Use 1 pound coffee cans.
Spray with Pam.
Fill cans half full.

title: chicken reuben
directions: Place breasts in pan with sauerkraut on top.
Top with cheese; pour dressing over all.
Cover and bake for 1 hour 10 minutes.

title: apple-glazed carrots
directions: Combine all ingredients. Heat and serve.

title: herbed grilled catfish
directions: Combine first seven ingredients.
Sprinkle mixture evenly on both sides of fillets.
Place fillets in a grilling basket coated with cooking spray.
Coat grill rack with cooking spray.
Place basket on rack.
Grill, covered, 4 minutes on each side or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Transfer to a serving platter.
If desired, garnish with oregano and thyme.
Yields 10 servings.

title: deer stew over rice
directions: Cut deer meat in pieces and brown.
Place in crock-pot.
Cover with water and then add remaining ingredients.
Cook overnight, then serve over rice.

title: tangy fruit and nut cole slaw
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; toss well.
Combine mayonnaise and remaining ingredients, stirring until smooth.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Toss well.
Chill covered.

title: tuna mold
directions: Heat soup in double boiler and add cream cheese.
Stir until smooth.
Add mayonnaise.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Add A. 1. steak sauce.
Blend together and cool.
When cool, add rest of ingredients.
Put in a mold that has been sprayed with Pam.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except cheese and potatoes.
Add potatoes and mix well.
Put in a casserole dish and top with shredded cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, covered, and 1/2 hour, uncovered.

title: german coleslaw
directions: Mix together oil and vinegar.
Bring to boil and pour over the cabbage, pepper, onion, sugar and salt.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Will keep 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: icebox gingerbread
directions: Beat sugar and Crisco/butter mixture in mixer. Add sorghum, then eggs (one at a time and beating between each one). Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk. Refrigerate batter. Will last for about a week. Bake amount you desire in muffin tins (lined with paper bake cups). Fill cups about 2/3's full. When you bake, add nuts and/or raisins if desired. Bake at 400° about 20 minutes.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add pineapple and blueberries.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and chill until set.

title: spinach salad
directions: Blend ingredients thoroughly in blender and refrigerate.

title: ritz torte pie
directions: Combine crackers, nuts, baking powder and vanilla.
Beat egg whites; add sugar and beat well.
Fold into cracker mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in greased 9-inch pie plate.
Cool. Put whipped cream or Cool Whip on top.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.

title: cinnamon hermits
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt and set aside. Cream sugar, shortening and spices. Beat in eggs. Blend in milk and raisins. Gradually stir in sifted flour mixture.
Drop teaspoonful onto lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 15-18 min. Makes 6 doz.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until done.
Slice off tops and spoon hot potatoes into bowl.
Break up potatoes with fork.
Lightly toss all ingredients together, reserving cheese for topping.
Place in baking pan.
Top with cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Add 2 cups boiling water to jello.
Add sherbet and mix until sherbet is dissolved.
Add drained fruit and pour into 10 x 13-inch pan.
Chill several hours.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Cook at 350°
for 45 minutes.

title: spinach omelet
directions: Combine spinach, broth, garlic and pepper in a small saucepan; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in Parmesan cheese; cook 1 minute or until cheese is melted, stirring constantly.
Set aside. Combine eggs and water; beat lightly.
Coat a 10-inch omelet pan or heavy skillet with cooking spray; add 1 teaspoon margarine. Place pan over medium heat until just hot enough to sizzle a drop of water.
Pour half of egg mixture into pan.
As mixture starts to cook, gently lift edges of omelet with a spatula and tilt pan so uncooked portion flows underneath.
When mixture is set, spread half of spinach mixture over half of omelet.
Loosen omelet with a spatula; fold in half and slide onto a warm serving platter. Repeat procedure with remaining ingredients.
Yield:
6 servings (about 180 calories per serving).

title: fruit cocktail dessert
directions: Sift sugar, flour and soda in a bowl. Add fruit cocktail and juice and then add beaten eggs.
Mix and pour into ungreased pan. Cover with brown sugar and pecans.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Put sugar, cocoa and milk in pan.
Cook as you would fudge, checking for hardness.
After mixture hardens into soft ball tested in water, add butter and vanilla.
Turn mixture off and add peanut butter and oatmeal.
Then drop onto tinfoil.
Cool and eat.

title: olive canapes
directions: Put olives and olive oil into a blender; puree.
Blend in remaining ingredients, except yolks and scallions.
Serve on crackers, or mound in a dish and serve crackers separately. Garnish with egg yolks and scallions.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Heat wok or large deep skillet over medium-high heat.
Add butter, onion and garlic and saute until onion is softened, about 2 minutes.
Mix in asparagus, mushrooms, cauliflower, zucchini and carrot and stir-fry 2 minutes.
(At this point, remove several pieces of asparagus tips, mushrooms and zucchini and reserve for garnish.)

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook chicken.
Let cool and pull from bone.
Cut pork into small pieces.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook slowly several hours.
Can be cooked in a crock-pot.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Combine apples and cider in 3-quart crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low 8 hours.
Puree in food sieve or food mill.
Return to pot; add sugar and spices.
Cover and cook on low 1 to 2 hours.
If thicker apple butter is desired, uncover and cook on high setting until desired consistency.
Apple butter will keep several weeks in refrigerator or may be frozen.

title: rice jamboree
directions: Cook onions in heated shortening until lightly browned.
Add beef and seasonings and cook until beef is brown.
Add peas and remaining ingredients to meat mixture.
Stir lightly.
Place in 2-quart greased covered casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Lay cucumber slices on a plate and sprinkle with vinegar. Cover and put on one side for 30 minutes.
Then drain in a sieve or colander to remove the excess liquid.
Butter the slices of bread.
Cover a slice of bread with slices of the drained cucumber, top with another slice of bread and press firmly together.
Cut off the crusts and cut each sandwich into triangles or fingers.
Arrange on a serving plate and garnish with sprigs of parsley.

title: taco salad
directions: Fry hamburger with onion until brown; drain.
Put in large bowl.
Add diced tomatoes, lettuce, cheese, chips and seasonings. Stir and serve.
Garnish with sour cream, salsa and any tummy pleasers you desire.
Enjoy!

title: pecan pie
directions: Use your favorite pecan pie recipe, but instead of the pecans, add 1 cup smooth peanut butter.
You can add a few chopped pecans, if desired.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook complete package of
frozen
mixed vegetables in 5 cups chicken broth and
tablespoons
chopped	onion
for
5 minutes. (Broth can be
canned
or made from bouillon cubes.) Thicken with flour mixed with
cup
milk.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: cheese triangles
directions: Separate pita bread into single sheets.
Place under broiler to warm.
Flip before toasted.
Remove when bread is hot, yet still soft.
Butter generously on inner side only.
Cut each circular side into eighths.
Sprinkle triangles with Parmesan cheese.
Place on foil and put under broiler.
Remove when toasted and crunchy. Serve warm or cold.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine all dry ingredients together; stir.
Add water, oil and nuts to the dry ingredients.
Fold in the pumpkin; mix well. Pour into 3 loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
May need slightly less time in the oven.

title: strawberries romanoff
directions: Sprinkle strawberries with powdered sugar; stir gently.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Just before serving, beat whipping cream in chilled bowl until stiff.
Stir in liqueur gradually.
Fold in strawberries.
Makes 6 servings.

title: terry's zucchini pie
directions: Mix oil, onion, eggs and salt in large bowl.
Add parsley, cheese and Bisquick.
Add zucchini and fold in.
Pour into sprayed glass pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tropical dream pie
directions: Combine cherry and pineapple juices to make 1/2 cup juice. Combine 2/3 cup sugar with flour; add the juice and cook until thick.
Stir in gelatins and continue stirring (while liquid is hot) until gelatin is thoroughly dissolved.
Add the fruits and pecans.
Pour into baked pie shells and place in the refrigerator until congealed thoroughly.
Serve with whipped cream on top.

title: mom's parkerhouse rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add milk, sugar, oil and salt. Add enough flour to make dough.
I sometimes use 1/2 of whole wheat flour along with the white flour.
Knead until smooth.
Let rise in a greased bowl.
Roll out to about 3/8-inch thick.
Cut with a round cookie cutter.
(I use a large mouth jar ring.)
Add a bit of margarine to each, fold in half and place on a cookie sheet.
Let rise again.
Bake at 375° until brown, 12 to 15 minutes.
Rub tops with margarine when you take out of oven.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery in a small amount of butter. Cook spaghetti in chicken broth. Arrange layer of spaghetti in large baking dish, then layer of sauteed vegetables.
Next layer of diced chicken. Top with mushroom soup.
(May be frozen at this stage.)
Top with shredded cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak (frozen) into 1/4-inch slices, approximately 3 inches long.
Cut and seed peppers into 1-inch cubes.
Shake and coat steak in cornstarch.
Cut onions into 1-inch cubes.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in water.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix together and let stand for 6 hours.
Will keep a week in refrigerator.

title: zucchini viennese
directions: Mix stuffing mix and melted butter.
Spread 1/2 of the mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sour cream and soup.
Spread zucchini slices in pan over the stuffing mix.
Spread soup mix over zucchini.
Top with cheese slices and spread remaining stuffing mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until zucchini reaches desired doneness.

title: idiot pie(any idiot can make it)
directions: Put dry pudding mix in bowl.
Dump in crushed pineapple and stir.
Add marshmallows and mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into a graham cracker pie crust.
Refrigerate 2 or 3 hours.
This makes 2 pies and will keep 2 weeks.
If desired, sprinkle with coconut.

title: house of representatives soup
directions: Cover beans in water and soak overnight.
Drain and re-cover with water.
Add a smoked ham hock and simmer slowly 4 hours or until beans are tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: zucchini triangles
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° until golden brown, about 25 minutes.
Cut into triangles.

title: quick 3-cup skillet cake
directions: Pour all into a mixing bowl and beat at high speed just until batter is smooth. Pour into a greased and floured skillet. Cook at 350° until light golden brown. Let sit for 5 minutes, then loosen edges and turn out upside down. Serve with favorite fruit and whipped cream.

title: pickled beets
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to boil.
Pour over beets and boil for 10 minutes, then pack in jars and seal.

title: shrimp and rice
directions: Combine all the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Halfway (30 minutes into baking time) take out of oven, stir and place back in oven.

title: hot diggity dog dish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Turn into a greased 2-quart baking dish. Cover.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Put in square pan in oven at 350° for about 20 minutes with butter, salt, pepper and onion salt. When done, put cheese over potatoes. Let melt and serve hot.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Blend flour, sugar, soda and salt in a large mixing bowl. Stir in cereal and add buttermilk and eggs.
Mix until all dry ingredients are moist.
Batter may be stored in refrigerator up to 6 weeks in a nonmetal bowl.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes in greased muffin tins filled 2/3's of the way full.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: goulash
directions: Brown ground chuck, mushrooms and chopped onion in a skillet until done.
Drain and pour into a large bowl.
Mix Ragu into ground meat mixture.
In a large casserole dish, layer half of meat and Ragu mixture in bottom of dish.
Add half the shredded cheese.
Layer remainder of meat and Ragu mixture over cheese and top off with rest of cheese on top.
Bake in a 350 degree oven for approximately 15 minutes until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat low speed for 1 minute.
Pour in floured and greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: crazy cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together all dry ingredients.
Add vanilla, vinegar, water and oil to mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes.
Ice with your favorite topping.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Put all ingredients in microwave bowl except nuts.
Microwave at Medium power for 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir in nuts; pour into greased 8 x 8-inch dish.
Refrigerate until set.
Cut into squares.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Make instant potato soup from first 3 ingredients.
Add soups, salt, pepper and broccoli.
Warm to desired temperature.
Serve.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Place popped corn in a large mixing bowl or roasting pan; set aside.
Combine sugar and corn syrup in medium saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 5 minutes.
Pour immediately over popcorn.
Stir gently with long spoon until all kernels are coated. (Be careful, mixture is hot and sticky and will burn you.)
Spread on waxed paper.

title: popovers
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease 8 (5 ounce) custard cups.
In medium bowl, with rotary beater, beat eggs, milk and oil until well combined.
Sift flour with salt over egg mixture; beat just until smooth.
Pour batter into prepared custard cups, filling each about half full.
Bake on large cookie sheet for 45 to 50 minutes or until deep golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: maple pecan waffles
directions: Preheat waffle iron. Sift flour with baking powder and salt.

title: polynesian ribs
directions: Simmer 3 hours in salted water.

title: caramel icing(make 1-2-3-4 cake)
directions: Cook and brown like you want it, stirring constantly.
Have ready 1 cup Carnation milk, warmed.
Add this to the butter and sugar mixture.
This will cause the mixture to be lumpy.
Cook slow and stir until it boils.
Cook about 10 minutes.
Take off heat and beat with mixer.
(I test by adding a few drops in cup of cold water.)

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on box.
Add cheese and 1/2 stick of butter to broccoli and stir until melted.
Pour mixture into casserole dish.
Crumble crackers on top of mixture. Melt remaining butter and then pour on top of crackers.
Cook in oven at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease pie plate, 9 or 10-inch. Beat all ingredients in a blender until smooth on high. Pour into pie plate. Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes. Garnish with whipping cream if desired.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar.
Add eggs; blend well.
Add flour, baking soda, salt and bananas.
Grease and flour loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: peanut butter-cream cheese pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add peanut butter and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Prepare Dream Whip according to directions and fold into mixture.
Turn into crust. Chill.

title: hot fudge topping
directions: Put all ingredients in a double boiler and just melt chocolate.
Do not cook.
This is to be used for hot fudge cake or ice cream.

title: baked spinach
directions: Cut bacon into 2-inch pieces and fry until crisp.
Drain on paper towels.
Wash fresh spinach, removing any tough stems and drain good.
If using frozen spinach, thaw.
Grease a shallow baking dish and arrange spinach over the bottom.
Sprinkle salt and pepper over it.
Alternate tomato and cheese slices over the spinach to cover it.
Sprinkle bacon on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 minutes or until the cheese is melted and the spinach tender.
Serves 6.

title: corn creole
directions: Saute corn, onions and green pepper in bacon fat for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and heat through.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar and salt. Cut shortening into this. Beat egg and add 1 cup warm water. Mix 1/4 cup warm water with 1 package yeast and
1 teaspoon sugar. Make a hole in the center of flour mixture and pour all liquids in hole. Stir (may now put in greased container and place in refrigerator).

title: sweet-sour red cabbage
directions: In a large bowl, stir the cider vinegar and sugars until sugars are dissolved. Add cabbage; toss to coat. Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: kirk's clam chowder
directions: Place potatoes in a saucepan and cover with water.
Bring to a boil; cover and cook until tender.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Melt
1/4 stick margarine and add all ingredients except 1/4 stick
margarine and cornflakes.
Mix well.
Put in baking dish. Melt
second
stick
of margarine.
Add cornflakes. Stir. Spread cornflake mixture on top.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°. May
add
sliced
mushrooms
to top of casserole, during last
10 minutes
of baking time.
Saute mushrooms in a little butter, for a few minutes beforehand.

title: shrimp steamed in beer
directions: Wash shrimp.
In large steamer, layer shrimp and lettuce. Pour beer over top.
Cover and heat to boiling.
Steam shrimp 15 to 20 minutes or until pink.
Drain shrimp, reserving 1/4 cup liquid.

title: recycled pickles
directions: Drain pickles; wash, slice thick.
Put back in jar and add all the other ingredients.
Shake until the sugar has dissolved. Set in refrigerator for 5 days before use.

title: taco salad
directions: Layer hamburger and lettuce with tomatoes and cheese.
Do not mix or add dressing and Doritos on top until time to serve.

title: mountain spoon bread
directions: Mix 1 cup hot water to 1 cup cornmeal.
Stir well.
Add shortening, salt and sugar.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add to mixture.
Add eggs last.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.
Spoon hot from pan to serve.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix the ingredients well.
Refrigerate.
Make the day before for best flavor.
Also use as a topping on baked potato.

title: butternut pie
directions: Mix cornstarch with water and set aside.
Combine sugar and milk in double boiler.
Bring almost to a boil, stirring constantly.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash and dry spinach.
Toss with hard-boiled eggs and crisp and crumbled bacon.

title: catfish court bouillon(coo by awn)
directions: Stew slowly for 2 hours.
Chop 2 pounds catfish into bite size chunks.
Add catfish to stew.
Simmer for 20 minutes without stirring.

title: ross russell's pickles
directions: Drain pickles in strainer.
Put pickles in large bowl.
Add sugar and Tabasco sauce; stir several times.
Let set overnight. Pickles may be put in small jars or back in gallon jar.

title: cherokee casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion; cook until onion is done.
Stir in seasonings, tomatoes, soup and rice.
Simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Put into baking dish.
Top with cheese and broil. Serves 3 to 4 people.

title: breakfast sausage casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Beat eggs.
Add mustard, salt and milk.
Add bread cubes and stir in cheese and sausage.
Set in refrigerator overnight in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° to 45 minutes.
Allow to stand before serving.

title: sally's shrimp stew
directions: In a large pot, boil potatoes and onion in the water until tender.
Do not drain off the water.
Add the soups and heat until soup dissolves.
Add shrimp and simmer until shrimp is red throughout.
Stir in pepper and horseradish.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine sour cream, cool whip, pudding and milk well with mixer. Layer cookies, bananas and pudding mixture in a bowl. Top with a few cookies. Keep refrigerated.

title: quick applesauce
directions: Peel, core and quarter apples.	Combine all ingredients in a pressure cooker.
Cover and bring up to high pressure.
Cook 1 minute.
Release pressure naturally.
Remove the cinnamon stick. Serve warm or chilled.
Makes 3 cups.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients together. Refrigerate.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: carrot and potato soup
directions: Serve hot or cold.
Melt butter in large saucepan, cook onion several minutes.
Add potatoes, carrots, salt and pepper and broth. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer for 30 minutes until vegetables are done.
Puree in blender.
Return to pan.
Add milk and heat to serving temperature if desired.
Garnish with shredded carrots.
Makes 8 servings.

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Spoon mixture into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until slightly firm.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Beat eggs, 1 cup sugar and spices until blended together.
Stir in remaining ingredients; beat well.
Pour into an unbaked 9-inch pie crust.
Cover with the other crust.
Make vents.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 300° and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: english pea salad
directions: Combine all of the ingredients and blend well.
Chill until served.
Serve on a bed of lettuce.

title: fresh garden omelet
directions: Grease omelet pan.
According to how many people you are serving, judge the number of eggs and milk to be used.
(Should be about like if you were to scramble an egg.)
Beat eggs well and add cheeses, tomatoes, bacon, onion, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder and peppers.
Mix all of this together well. Pour equal amounts in each side of omelet pan.
Cook on top of range for approximately 7 minutes, then place in 350° oven for an additional 7 minutes or until omelet is done.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Marinate meat for 3 or 4 hours, turning several times.
This is great for steak or for chicken to cook on the grill.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Bring to a boil and brush on chicken or other meat desired.

title: rhubarb coffee cake
directions: Cream brown sugar and butter.
Add egg and mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with combined buttermilk and vanilla.
Stir in rhubarb.
Stir in nuts if being used.
Pour into greased 8 x 12-inch or 9 x 14-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup granulated sugar mixed with cinnamon.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: gwen's green enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Cook ground beef until no longer pink.
Drain liquid from beef.
Layer as you would lasagna. Beginning with beef mixture, tortillas, then cheese ending with cheese.
Cook for 30 minutes in 350 degree oven.

title: hawaiian banana bread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients into a bowl.
Combine the shortening and the dry ingredients with your fingers.
Puree the bananas and add to the flour and shortening, along with the well-beaten eggs. Fold the liquid into the dry very quickly (do not overmix).
The batter should resemble muffin batter.
Place into loaf pan and bake at 350° until a toothpick is inserted into the middle and comes out clean.
Remove from pan and cool on a rack.

title: ma's potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together in a 2-quart baking dish.
Cook for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: nut and raisin cake
directions: Cook 1 box of raisins with enough water to reserve 1 cup of juice after raisins have simmered about 15 minutes.
Set aside to cool.
Mix the sugar, butter and eggs.
In a large bowl, mix the flour, soda, cinnamon, salt and vanilla.
Mix this to egg mixture with 1 cup raisin juice.
Stir in (by hand) all the raisins, and as many nuts (1 cup or more) as you like.
Bake at 325° in tube pan for about 1 hour or until done.
This can be stirred by hand, and it keeps well.

title: blueberry streusel pie
directions: Combine sour cream, 3/4 cup sugar, egg, 2 tablespoons flour, vanilla and salt in a large bowl; beat at medium speed with electric mixer 5 minutes or until smooth.
Fold in berries.
Spoon into pastry shell.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: sweet and sour hot dogs
directions: Simmer jelly and mustard in crock-pot, then add hot dogs.

title: homemade reeces candy
directions: Mix peanut butter and confectioners sugar. Add melted margarine. Shape in small balls. Chill for 1 hour or longer. Then melt chocolate and paraffin. (I use a bamboo skewer to dip each ball.) Place on wax paper. Roll in chopped nuts if you like nuts after dipping in chocolate. Refrigerate or freeze. Makes about 75.

title: mother's carrot cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt. Combine oil and sugar and mix well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Gradually add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add 2 cups grated carrots and nuts.
Pour into 3 (8-inch) pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together and bake in unbaked pie shell at 350°
for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook and crumble bacon.
Wash and cut broccoli into bite size pieces.
Put into a large container with the raisins, sunflower seeds and bacon.

title: fruit juice fizz
directions: Cut orange or lemon into slices.
Put one or two cups of juice into the pitcher.
Add 3 more cups of juice for every cup of seltzer or club soda.
Chill juice.

title: mississippi cornbread salad
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, dressing mix and sour cream.
Set aside.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash with onions according to directions, omitting salt; drain well, pressing between paper towels.
Combine squash mixture, mayonnaise and next 4 ingredients in lightly greased 2-quart pan.
Combine crackers or bread crumbs and butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: apple quickie
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Spread into greased 9 x 12-inch pan; pour on topping.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jeff davis pie
directions: Mix together and pour into unbaked pie shell, either 10-inch or 2 (8-inch).
Bake 1 hour at 300° or until done in the middle.

title: roast pork fried rice
directions: Using
a high flame, heat a well greased frying pan and add salt.
Scramble egg, add roast pork, onions, bean sprouts and rice.
Stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add soy sauce, m.s.g. and pepper. Cook
and stir for 1 minute.
Can use chicken, turkey or ham in place of pork.

title: four layer hamburger and macaroni casserole
directions: Combine beef and seasoning mix in a large skillet. Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, 2 to 3 minutes or until beef is done. Combine one package of macaroni and cheese and sour cream in a bowl. Spread over bottom of an 8-inch square baking dish. Top with beef mixture. Spread remaining package of macaroni and cheese over beef and top with tomatoes, nacho chips and cheese to cover casserole. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Combine cooked chicken, broccoli, soup and water chestnuts. Put in greased 8x8 pan. Top with cheese slices. Combine bisquick and butter, sprinkle over cheese. Bake at 400 degrees for one hour or until hot and bubbly. To double batch use a 9x13 pan.

title: aunt ruth's bread pudding
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and milk.
Add crumbs.
Dot with butter. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in greased casserole in 375° oven until knife slid in middle comes out clean.

title: bacon 'n' egg casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Arrange bread cubes over bottom of pan. Sprinkle with cheese and top with 2 ounces bacon.
In medium mixing bowl beat together milk, eggs and seasonings; pour egg mixture into pan and sprinkle with remaining 2 ounces bacon.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes (until top is browned and knife inserted in center, comes out clean).

title: chili con carne
directions: Cook the ground beef and onion until brown.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer until liquid is rather thick.

title: weight watchers pancake
directions: Beat egg, add a little milk, cinnamon and mix with bread. Grate small apple.
Spray pan with Pam, pour batter on pan, put grated apple on top.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: cyclop's cookies
directions: In large bowl, beat margarine and peanut butter with mixer for 30 seconds.
Add sugars, beating until fluffy.
Add egg, milk and vanilla, beating well.
Sift together dry ingredients.
On low speed, add flour mixture to peanut butter mixture, beating well. Chill for 1 + hours for easy handling.
Heat oven to 375°.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in additional white sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until edges are firm.
Immediately press chocolate Kisses on top of each cookie.
Place cookies on cooling rack to cool.

title: rainbow jello salad
directions: Mix each of the jellos with 1/2 cup hot water.
Add pineapple to the lime jello.
Add juice and enough water to make up 1 1/2 cups cool water.
Add the cream cheese to the lemon jello.
Mix well, then add 1 1/2 cups cold water.
When halfway set up, put in dish.
Put red in first, then spoon in lemon and then put lime on top.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add water and Mazola; mix quickly into dry ingredients.
Toss onto floured board and roll to desired thickness.
This recipe makes one small double-crust pie.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and layer with sliced onions in glass jars. Prepare mixture of remaining ingredients and pour over cold; do not cook or boil anything.
Cover and refrigerate for 5 days. Pickles will then be ready to use.
Keep in fridge.

title: homemade eagle brand
directions: When baking chocolate cakes, try dusting greased cake pans with cocoa instead of flour, so the dark cake is not spotted on the bottom.

title: puffed rice balls
directions: Bring ingredients to boil.
Cook to soft ball stage.
In a large bowl (I spray with pan coating, Pam), pour in puffed rice while mixture is cooking.
Pour over puffed rice.
Mix.
Rinse hands in cold water; form balls.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, milk, eggs, cream of tartar, soda, salt and vanilla.
Add flour to make a soft dough.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix together flour and sugar and press in 9 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Cream together cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip and spread mixture over crust.
Mix lemon pudding mix and milk until thick.
Spread mixture over cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and grated walnuts.
Chill.

title: triple by-pass chocolate cake
directions: Mix and bake chocolate cake mix according to package directions into 2 round layers.
Cool.
Pour the can of condensed milk evenly over each layer -- 1/2 per layer.
Place first layer on serving plate and spread one half of frosting on top only. Repeat with second layer and place on top of first.
Whip cream with the sugar, until stiff peaks form.
Spread over entire cake. Shave Skor bar over the top.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Cream cheese and margarine.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.

title: pineapple cake no. 1
directions: Mix sugar, flour, baking soda and salt.
Add eggs and pineapple; mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
In small mixing bowl, mix brown sugar and nuts; then sprinkle over cake batter. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
While cake is baking, bring oleo, milk, sugar and vanilla to rolling boil in saucepan.
Pour this over hot cake when it's done.
Let cool.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, egg, salt, milk, pumpkin and spice in food processor.
Process until well combined, then add water and process.
Pour over baked crust and bake about 50 minutes or until filling is barely set in center.

title: chocolate chex treat
directions: Pour cereal into large bowl and set aside.
Melt chocolate chips in microwave until partly melted.
Add peanut butter and butter; melt completely.
Stir.
Pour hot, melted mixture over Chex and stir carefully until all Chex are coated.
(This will take several minutes; a rubber spatula works best.)

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Beat eggs.
Stir in and blend other ingredients.
Chill for 1 hour.
Drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix water and yeast until dissolved.
Add cake mix and flour. Mix well.
Knead 3 to 5 minutes.
Put in greased bowl and let rise until double in bulk.
Roll out dough about 1/2-inch thick. Spread 1/4 cup oleo on top.
Sprinkle with 1 cup brown sugar.
Add 2 teaspoons cinnamon, nuts or raisins may also be spread on top. Roll jelly roll style and cut 1-inch thick.
Put in pan and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry yum-yum
directions: Combine blueberries, 1 cup sugar and water in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until berries are soft.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Saute onion and ground beef until meat loses redness; season with 1 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Place meat and onion mixture in 2-quart casserole dish; cover with soup.
Cook potatoes until soft; mash with butter and milk.
Season with remaining salt. Spoon mashed potatoes over meat mixture.
Bake at 425° until bubbly.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except tomatoes and lettuce leaves. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Then when ready to serve, cut tomatoes in half, making zigzag, cutting to make 6 halves.
Then put on lettuce leaves.
Top with shrimp salad, divided into 6 equal portions.

title: divinity candy
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until threads make soft ball in water.
Add to beaten egg whites.
Add vanilla and nuts.

title: ham slice
directions: Cover with cranberry sauce and bake about 30 minutes in 350° oven.
The sauce does not run off.

title: strawberry almond crepes
directions: Use the basic crepes recipe. Prepare crepes ahead of time. Fill crepes with lightly sweetened strawberries, lay them side by side in a chafing dish, in which you melted the butter in. Sprinkle with almonds and warm thoroughly. Top with whip cream.

title: grandma wangner german stollen or hot cross buns
directions: Combine the milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Let cool. Combine yeast and water.
Add to cool milk mixture. Add 1/2 flour.
Mix on low speed.
Add well beaten eggs.
Mix on low speed.
Add enough flour to make soft dough. Add 1 cup floured raisins (if desired, also 1 cup each of cordial fruits, cherries and 1/4 cup slivered almonds).
Mix by hand.
Put dough on lightly floured table.
Knead until smooth.
Put in ungreased bowl large enough to let dough double in size.
Set in warm place, covered with light cloth (I put in oven and keep hot water in pan under bowl).

title: pink salad
directions: Mix lemon juice and milk together.
Add other ingredients. Drain pineapple and oranges.
Chill.

title: new tuna noodle casserole
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°. In a stockpot, bring 4 quarts of water to a boil. Partially cook noodles in the boiling water for half the time given in the package direction. Meanwhile, grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole. In a large bowl, combine cream cheese, sour cream and milk until smooth and creamy. Stir in flaked tuna, chopped green onions and chopped bell pepper. Season with salt and pepper. Drain the noodles thoroughly and stir them into the tuna mixture. Place the noodles in the prepared casserole and sprinkle with cheese. Bake until the mixture is bubbly and the top is browned, about 25 minutes and serve.

title: peach crunch
directions: Arrange peaches in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan that has been greased.
Crumble other ingredients and sprinkle over peaches. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with cream or half and half.

title: deep sea chowder
directions: Gradually add macaroni and 1 tablespoon salt to rapidly boiling water
so
that water continues to boil.
Cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally, until tender.
Drain in colander; run cold water through them.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar and beer.
Place mixture in loaf pan.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Pour butter over bread and bake 10 more minutes or until done.

title: apricot salad
directions: In small sauce pan, combine jello, sugar, and water.
Bring to a boil.
Stir and dissolve well.
Remove from heat.
Add baby food and pineapple with juice.
Stir and set aside for 10 minutes. In a small bowl, mix cream cheese and Cool Whip until smooth. Pour into fruit mixture and mix together.
Stir in pecans and refrigerate until firm.

title: top of stove meat loaf
directions: Thoroughly mix beef, crumbs, 1/4 cup soup, onion, egg and seasonings.
Shape firmly into 2 loaves; brown on both sides in skillet in shortening.
Cover; cook over low heat for 25 minutes. Spoon off fat.
Pour remaining soup mixed with water and mustard on loaves; top with cheese.
Cook for 10 minutes, uncovered. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: liver burgers
directions: In meat grinder, alternate liver, onions and bacon into bowl. Add to liver mixture salt, pepper, egg, flour and any seasonings you wish to add.
Mix together thoroughly.
In frying pan, put just enough shortening to wet bottom of pan.
Burgers will make their own grease (or just a tiny bit).
(This mixture will be a little runny, but flour and egg will help hold it together; sometimes I add a little extra flour.)

title: black forest pie
directions: Spread 1 cup of Cool Whip on bottom of pie crust.
Combine milk and pudding mix; blend at low speed for 1 minute.
Fold in 1 1/2 cups of Cool Whip.
Spread over layer in crust.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over top, leaving a 1-inch border and forming a depression in the center.
Spoon in cherry pie filling and chill for at least 3 hours.
Garnish with grated chocolate.

title: meat loaf with oats
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients with 1/2 teaspoon salt in saucepan, mixing well.
Cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Combine ground beef with 1 teaspoon salt, half the tomato sauce mixture and remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Shape into loaf in shallow baking pan.
Pour remaining tomato sauce mixture over meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: potato medley
directions: This recipe is a hearty mixture which includes an important vegetable, namely yams, that should be more frequently used since it is one of the few easily available and inexpensive yellow vegetables in the American diet.
When mixed with the most popular vegetable, white potatoes, it becomes an appealing accompaniment to a variety of proteins and salads.

title: pasta salad
directions: Combine oil, lemon juice, Accent and seasoned salt. Pour over cooked pasta and let sit overnight.
Combine pasta with remaining ingredients. Chill before serving.

title: seven layer bars
directions: First layer must be melted margarine (melt margarine and let sit for 15 minutes).
Then, add remaining ingredients layer after layer.
Final layer must be condensed milk.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Put in refrigerator until chilled.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown meat, pepper and onion in a skillet.
Cook noodles until done.
Mix together with sauce.
Place in a lasagna pan.
Decorate top with cheese and pepperoni.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.
May be made ahead of time, but heat long enough to make sure that it is served hot.
Can be separated into small portions and frozen.
Can add some chopped pepperoni, taco seasoning or oregano, to meat mixture for more flavor.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar, flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Mix as pie crust and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: 5 flavor cake
directions: Cream oleo and shortening with sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs; combine flour and baking powder.
Add to cream mixture, alternately with milk.
Stir in flavorings.
Spoon mixture into 10-inch tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until tests done.
Add glaze and leave in pan 10 minutes.

title: parsnip stew
directions: Chop pork fine and put through grinder.
Pare potatoes and parsnips; slice.
Put one layer of pork, one layer of potatoes and one layer of parsnip.
Repeat until all are used.
Cover with cold water; season with pepper and salt.
Cook 45 minutes.
Note: Cost, including gas heat, = $0.2137 in 1917 terms.
From Telegram Conservation Cook Book, page 91.

title: hot dog chili for a crowd
directions: Brown ground beef in heavy kettle, breaking up with fork, stirring until almost done.
Add all spices and dried onions.
Mix well and add tomato sauce and water.
Cover and simmer for about 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Makes enough for 216 hot dogs.

title: sweet relish
directions: Grind tomatoes, onions, peppers and celery.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons of the salt over this mixture and let stand 1 hour. Drain well and add the rest of the ingredients.
Bring to boil and simmer 15 minutes.
Put in sterilized jars and seal.
Can use all green peppers.

title: surprise cheese puffs appetizer
directions: Blend together well. Form into small balls around a stuffed olive and place on a cookie sheet. Place in freezer until frozen. When ready to serve, bake for 10 minutes in a moderately hot oven (425°). When puffs are frozen, they may be placed in a plastic bag and used as needed. Do not thaw before baking. Makes 30 medium puffs.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add eggs and pineapple.
Lastly, add nuts.
Pour into an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes (until toothpick comes out clean).

title: pineapple-cream-custard cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Pour the pineapple on top.
In blender, blend the cream cheese and vanilla instant pudding. Spread on top
of cake.
Spread Cool Whip on top of cake. Sprinkle coconut on top.

title: mandarin spinach salad
directions: Combine the above ingredients using oranges and almonds as toppings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and squeeze spinach until dry. Mix all ingredients well. Cover;
refrigerate
at
least
hours.
Stir
before serving. Good served with rye or wheat round bread, torn into pieces.

title: cherry macaroon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Pour pie filling into the unbaked pie shell (deep pie shell works best).
Beat together egg and evaporated milk.
Add sugar, flour, salt, almond extract and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in coconut.
Pour over pie filling.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until puffed and light brown.
Cool well before serving.

title: week in chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in lightly greased casserole dish.
Combine cream of mushroom soup and onion soup mix and spoon over chicken.
Cover casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 2. Ingredients may be increased when serving more than two.

title: ginger cookies and decorating icing
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, shortening, molasses and vinegar.
Bring to a boil; cook 2 minutes, stirring occasionally. Cool.
Sift together the flour, salt, soda, baking powder and spices.
In a large mixing bowl, mix together the eggs and cooled molasses mixture.
Add dry ingredients, about 2 cups at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Divide the dough into thirds; wrap in waxed paper and thoroughly chill (about 2 hours or overnight).
On a well floured board, roll out the dough 1/4-inch thick.
Cut in shape desired with cutter dipped in flour each time.
Place cookies 1 inch apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes a few dozen cookies.

title: baked whole onions
directions: Slice top and bottom off onions.
Arrange in 9 inch glass dish. Place 1/2 teaspoon of oleo on each onion.
Sprinkle with paprika. Microwave on high, covered for 6-8 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press rolls onto large cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix.
Spread onto crust.
Layer all raw vegetables and cheese.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. In a medium bowl, sift the first 4 ingredients together; set aside. Mix the sugars and butter until creamy at medium speed, then high speed. Scrape bowl. Add eggs to the creamed sugar mixture and beat until smooth. Add flour mixture to the creamed mixture. Mix until smooth. Add oats, vanilla, coconut and nuts. Mix until smooth. Drop on ungreased baking sheet. Bake 10 minutes. Yields 5 dozen.

title: sauerkraut hot dish #1
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add salt and pepper.
Put half of ground beef mixture in casserole.
Add all sauerkraut, then rest of ground beef.
Then add cooked noodles and soups over top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Put cheese on top and bake 20 minutes more. Serve with your favorite breads.

title: overnight pancakes
directions: In a small bowl, dissolve yeast in water:
let stand for 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, in a large bowl combine the dry ingredients. Beat eggs, buttermilk and oil;
stir into dry ingredients just until moistened.
Stir in yeast mixture.
Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight.
To make pancakes, pour batter by 1/4 cupfuls onto a greased HOT griddle;
turn when bubbles form on top of pancakes.
Cook until second side is golden brown.
Yield:
about 2 1/2 dozen.
Keeps for weeks in refrigerator.

title: chocolate cupcakes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line muffin pans with paper baking cups. In medium saucepan, melt corn oil spread.
Remove from heat; stir in sugar.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add alternately with buttermilk and add vanilla to mixture in saucepan. Beat with a whisk until well blended.
Spoon into baking cups. Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from pans to wire rack; cool completely. Sift powdered sugar over cupcakes.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Boil pork.
Marinate the pork in mixture of soy sauce, sugar and sherry.
Dredge the marinated pork in cornstarch and fry. Stir-fry vegetables in oil.
Mix pork, vegetables and Sweet and Sour Sauce together; serve hot with rice.

title: date nut bread
directions: Mix dates, soda and boiling water; let stand.
Mix together other ingredients except nuts.
Add date-water mixture 1/3 at a time, mixing well.
Fold nuts in by hand.
Bake in 3 loaf pans for 1 hour at 325°.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Mix together and leave overnight to ripen.

title: frosted bites
directions: Thaw pastry for 20 minutes at room temperature or overnight in the refrigerator.
Unfold pastry.
Cut on the 3 fold lines. Then cut each piece crosswise into 7 rectangles (21 total). Arrange pastry rectangles on an ungreased baking sheet.
Prick several times with a fork.
Bake in a 425° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until light brown.
Transfer to a wire rack.
Stir 3 to 4 teaspoons water into chocolate frosting.
Spoon frosting over tops of warm pastries.
Immediately sprinkle with nuts.
Cool thoroughly.
Makes 21 pastries.

title: biscuits and beef
directions: Place one set of biscuit halves in bottom of baking dish. Saute' ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Add chili powder, garlic salt, shredded cheese (save 3/4 c. for top), sour cream, egg and tomato sauce.
Stir together and pour over biscuits. Place remaining biscuits on top and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: ripe tomato jam
directions: Grind tomatoes,
apples
and
orange together.	Add the sugar and cook until
it thickens.
Add 1 package orange jello for flavor.
Stir and put in sterilized jars.
Seal.

title: cranberry fluff
directions: Combine cranberries, marshmallows and sugar.
Cover and chill overnight.
Add apples, grapes, walnuts and salt.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill.
Turn into serving bowl or spoon into individual lettuce cups.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: quick bean soup
directions: Combine celery, carrots, onion, 2 cups water and bouillon cubes.
Bring to boil, then simmer 10 minutes.
Add black pepper, hot pepper sauce, additional cup of water and Bush's Best Great Northern beans.
Bring to boil again; simmer 5 minutes longer. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: date and nut loaf
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix together walnuts and dates. Add egg yolks and dry ingredients.
Add egg whites last. Bake in loaf pans at 325° for one hour.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix boiling water and Jell-O until dissolved.
Add strawberries, marshmallows and pineapple.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and chill before adding the topping.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
Bake 1/2 the mix in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan at 350°
for 15 minutes.
In top of double boiler, melt together, butter, caramels and condensed milk.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Pour over baked 1/2 of cake.
Pour remaining 1/2 of cake batter on top. Sprinkle with pecans and chocolate chips.
Bake additional 25 minutes at 350°.

title: hot chipped beef
directions: Mix
together and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with Ritz crackers or other snack crackers.

title: chicken breasts in mushroom sauce
directions: Combine mushrooms and onions in 1-quart casserole dish. Cover.
Microwave at High 3 to 4 minutes or until mushrooms are tender.
Drain well.
Place margarine in glass 4 cup measuring cup.
Microwave at High 30 seconds to 1 1/2 minutes or until melted.
Blend in flour.
Add sherry, water, yogurt, salt, pepper and bouillon.
Stir in mushrooms and onions.
Arrange chicken in an 8 x 8-inch microwave-safe dish.
Pour sauce over chicken. Cover with wax paper.
Microwave at Medium for 14 to 20 minutes or until sauce thickens and chicken is tender and no longer pink. Turn and rearrange chicken and stir sauce every 5 minutes during cooking.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Combine beef, bread crumbs, onion, eggs, catsup, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, thyme, salt and pepper in a large bowl.
Shape into a 10 x 4-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: little fruit pies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening until like fine meal.
Add water slowly until dough is easy to roll.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Drain oysters.
Remove any remaining pieces of shell particles. Combine cracker crumbs, butter, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle 1/3 of crumb mixture in bottom of well-greased 1-quart casserole dish. Cover with a layer of oysters.
Repeat layers.
Add Worcestershire sauce to milk and pour over contents of dish.
Sprinkle remaining crumb mixture on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until brown.
Serves 6.

title: mexican breakfast eggs
directions: Crumble sausage in skillet and brown.
Add onion, garlic, green pepper and cumin seed.
Cook until onions are soft.
Add Ro-Tel to sausage, then salt and pepper to taste.
Stir well.
With large spoon, make a well in sausage mixture and break egg into well. Repeat with remaining eggs.
Cover with tight lid and cook until eggs are firm.
Remove lid and sprinkle mixture with cheese. Continue to cook until cheese is melted.

title: deep dark chocolate cake with cream cheese chocolate frosting
directions: Combine all dry ingredients; add all other ingredients except boiling water.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes; fold in boiling water.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fiesta salad
directions: *Can substitute cooked beef, pork or chicken.

title: banana rolled oat cookies
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon into mixing bowl.
Cut in butter.
Add egg, bananas, rolled oats and nutmeats and beat until thoroughly blended.
Drop by teaspoonfuls, about 1 1/2-inches apart, onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: linguini salad
directions: Cook noodles, drain and rinse well with cold water.
Add Salad Supreme and Parmesan cheese to taste.
Add tomatoes, cucumbers and green pepper.
Add onion to taste.
Mix well with Italian dressing.
Use enough to coat vermicelli well.

title: garlic-artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Spoon into a baking dish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve with crackers or French bread.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar and flour.
Add eggs, vanilla and buttermilk.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) unbaked pie crusts.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cover edges of pie crust with aluminum foil to prevent browning too fast.

title: yam a dandy
directions: Crumble ingredients and put on top of potatoes. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: rhubarb-apricot jam
directions: Cook apricots until tender. Add rhubarb, cook until done. Measure cooked fruit. Add 1 c. sugar to each cup of fruit. Cook until thick. Pour into sterilized containers. Seal.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix and bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish, except potato chips.
Top with crushed potato chips and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: hawaiian muffins
directions: Combine muffin mix and 1/2 cup flaked coconut.
Drain crushed pineapple, reserving 1 tablespoon syrup.
Add pineapple, beaten egg and 2/3 cup milk to dry ingredients.
Blend only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full. Bake in hot oven (400°) for 15 to 20 minutes, or until done.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add reserved pineapple syrup; beat well.
Serve with hot muffins.
Makes 12 to 16 muffins.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Combine all ingredients, except broccoli, in 2-quart microproof bowl.
Stir until cornstarch is dissolved.
Add broccoli.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook on 70 for 13 to 14 minutes or until broccoli is fork-tender.
Stir once during cooking time.
Let stand 3 minutes before serving.
Garnish with small raw broccoli florets.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Cooking Time: 13 to 14 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan (glass not recommended).
Combine corn muffin mix, onion, cottage cheese and broccoli, drained.
Add melted margarine. Mix thoroughly.
Bake in pan used for melting margarine.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, until top is lightly browned.

title: alligator sauce piquante
directions: Marinate meat overnight in Italian dressing, salt, red pepper, garlic powder and meat tenderizer.
Add flour to oil to make a roux and cook until brown.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix carrots and raisins.
Add sugar to mayonnaise and mix well.
Add to carrots and raisins and refrigerate.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mary's candied yams
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Boil water, sugar, butter and nutmeg. Add potatoes.
Cut heat back and boil very lightly.
If you boil hard, they come all to pieces.
Boil about 45 minutes to 1 hour. Stick toothpick in and see if they are soft; they are done.
If potatoes get done before your juice thickens, take potatoes out and thicken juice.
If too thick before potatoes are done, add a little water.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain vegetables and mix.
Mix vinegar, sugar and salad oil together.
Boil until clear, about 1 minute.
Pour hot over the vegetables.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cool.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: shrimp cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese, celery, garlic, soy sauce and pepper sauce.
Stir in shrimp.
Shape mixture into ball.
Chill 4 to 24 hours.
Before serving, coat with parsley.

title: zucchini souffle
directions: Steam rice in 2 cups water.

Chop onion and saute in margarine. When rice and onion have cooled, mix all ingredients. Put in greased 8-inch square baking pan and top with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cool slightly before cutting.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Crush Oreos and mix with margarine.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Freeze for approximately 2 hours.
Put softened ice cream layered on top; freeze for 10 minutes.
Put syrup on top; freeze for 10 minutes.
Spread Cool Whip on top and freeze.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Mix all dry ingredients. Add milk and shortening. Bring to a hard boil. Boil 1 minute, then set aside to cool. Add vanilla and beat until smooth.

title: creek bank potatoes
directions: Use foil and Dutch oven if not cooking in coals or on grill.

title: best doggone pancakes
directions: Mix oil, egg and 1 cup milk.
Sift dry ingredients and add to the mixture.
Then add 2 tablespoons more milk.
Fry on hot griddle.

title: chicken pot pie ii
directions: In a medium saucepan, melt margarine over medium heat. Add onion; cook 2 minutes. Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Stir in broth and milk. Cook, stirring constantly, until bubbly and thickened. Add chicken and vegetables. Remove from heat and spoon into crust. Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pat's chocolate nut chews
directions: Combine in saucepan first 4 ingredients.
Stir until butter melts and cook over medium heat, let boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper or buttered cookie sheet.

title: corn bread
directions: Heat oil.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour in oil.
Stir.
Pour in pan and bake at 450° until brown or done.

title: chocolate mess
directions: In a large see through compote type bowl, crumble half of the chocolate sheet cake.
Next, layer half of the chocolate mousse, then sprinkle half of the smashed up Heath bars, then cover with half of the fluffy, thawed Cool Whip.
Repeat the entire layering, finishing with any leftover smashed up Heath bars.
Chill to set. Enjoy!

title: chinese style ribs(crock-pot)
directions: Mix all ingredients except ribs.
Brush mixture on both sides of ribs.
Place ribs in crock-pot.
Pour remaining sauce over ribs.
Place cover on crock-pot and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.

title: good nutrition chocolate pie
directions: Lightly grease sides and bottom of 9-inch pie pan.
Crush flakes with rolling pin.
In a bowl, stir sugar into flakes.
Melt butter and slowly add to cereal, mixing thoroughly.
Press mixture firmly into bottom and sides of pie pan.
Chill.
Make chocolate pudding with milk, using package directions.
Chill 10 minutes. Fold in bananas and nuts; fill pie shell.
Top with cream or other topping.
Serves 8.

title: liz's fudge
directions: Melt all ingredients (except nuts) until smooth.
Add nuts. Put in 9 x 9-inch waxed papered pan.
Refrigerate 2 hours and cut.

title: kid's peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the egg and sugar. Add peanut butter.
Mix well.
Roll into marble size balls.
Press with fork. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 10 to 12 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: sugarless spice cake
directions: Cook raisins
and prunes in 2 cups water until water is gone. Cool.
(Chgs.
prunes.)	Beat
eggs
and
applesauce together. Mix
in other ingredients.	Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan.
Cool.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Mix tomatoes and salt.
Let stand 12 hours.
Drain.
Heat vinegar, sugars and spices to a boil.
Add onions; boil gently for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and peppers; bring slowly to a boil. Simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally with a wooden spoon.
Pack in hot jars.
Be sure to cover vegetables with syrup.
Process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and add remaining ingredients.
Mix together and let stand 24 hours.
(This keeps 6 weeks in refrigerator.)
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pancit canton(stir-fry)
directions: *If green beans are unavailable, use broccoli spears or sliced cabbage.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt, flour and cocoa.
Add milk gradually and cook until thick on low (can cook in microwave).
Stir every 2 minutes. When slightly thick, add egg yolks and cook until thick.
Add butter and vanilla. Pour in baked pie shells.
Add meringue.
Cook at 375° until brown.

title: watermelon delight
directions: Cut melon in chunks; remove seeds and process in blender until chunks are broken but not pureed. Run through food mill to remove fiber. Add lemon juice and sugar. Serve with ice. Garnish with melon balls and lemon slices. Do not keep longer than a day or two.

title: mama's pinto bean cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add beaten egg and mashed beans. Sift all dry ingredients together; add sugar mixture.
Add apples, raisins, chopped nuts and vanilla.
Pour into well-greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Glaze and decorate with maraschino cherries and walnuts.

title: cheese buns(great for sandwiches)
directions: In a mixing bowl, put in order given (except cheese and 2 cups flour).
Beat at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Stir in cheese and 2 cups flour to make a firm dough.
Cover; let rest 15 minutes. Toss on a well floured surface until no longer sticky.
Divide into 12 to 16 parts.
Shape into flat buns.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Cover and let rise in warm place until very light or doubled, about 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Place carrots and 2 tablespoons of water in a 2-quart microwave-safe utensil.
Cover with Glad wrap and microwave at Full power for 10 minutes or until carrots are tender, but crisp. Let stand covered for 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Add onion rings and green pepper strips.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, nutmeg and salt.
Add to the beaten eggs. Mix until smooth.
Stir in the rhubarb.
Put in 9-inch pastry shell and dot with butter.
Put top pastry shell on.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: golden brown oven-fried chicken
directions: Combine
sour cream, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, celery salt, paprika, salt and pepper;
mix well.
Dip chicken breasts in
sour
cream
mixture
and dredge in stuffing mix. Place chicken
in
a
lightly
greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Drizzle with margarine and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 8 servings.

title: orange breakfast ring
directions: Combine sugar and orange rind.
Separate biscuits; dip each in butter and coat with sugar mixture.
Stand biscuits on sides, overlapping edges, in a 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove ring from pan and invert on serving platter.

title: best-in-the-west beans
directions: Brown meats and drain. Add onion and cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients except beans.
Mix well. Add beans.
Pour into 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stromboli
directions: Allow dough to thaw at room temperature, about 1 hour.
Pull dough lengthwise.
Stretch each loaf to form a rectangle about 6 x 12-inches.
Down center of rectangle, layer 1/2 the ham, salami, cheeses, onions and mushrooms, if desired.
Be sure to overlap ingredients among layers.
Sprinkle with oregano and basil.
Fold both sides of dough to meet at middle.
Pinch seams together. Repeat with 2nd rectangle and remaining ingredients.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Slice and serve immediately.
Build your own for your family's taste.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Toss apple, celery and nuts with mayonnaise.
Add a little sugar and lemon juice.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; put into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: Blend together. Goes great with all kinds of fruit.

title: baked hamburgers in sauce
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients into patties.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Thin tomato paste with a little tomato juice.
Add pinch of sugar; bring to a boil.
Pour tomato paste mixture over burgers. Bake in a 375° oven until sauce begins to brown and burgers are brown on top.
Carefully turn burgers to brown bottom.

title: coffee pecan cake
directions: In a bowl, beat sugar and egg yolks until light.
Gently fold in nuts and bread crumbs, then stir in coffee.
In another bowl, whisk egg whites until soft peaks form; fold into mixture.
Pour into round cake form and bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until well risen and firm to touch.
Cool on wire rack.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix well.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pie crusts.

title: beef-potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes with onion, salt and pepper.
Put in bottom of casserole dish.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: In saucepan, melt butter over very low heat.
Stir in evaporated milk, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Remove pan from heat and gradually add the sifted powdered sugar.
Work with hands until a dough consistency is reached.
Add peanut butter and corn syrup. Mix well.
Shape dough into balls, dip in chocolate and roll in peanuts.
Refrigerate until firm.
