Makes 48 balls.

title: 4-layer dessert
directions: Mix together and pour on top of cream cheese mixture. Top with Cool Whip; may add chopped nuts, if desired.

title: broiled deviled hamburgers
directions: Mix and spread on buns.
Put in broiler 3 inches from unit for about 6 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie(serves 6)
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water and allow to stand.
Put egg yolks, lemon juice and 1/2 cup sugar in upper part of a double boiler. Beat with beater until mixed well.
Place over rapidly boiling water and beat constantly until very light, thick and creamy. Remove from stove burner; add gelatine and stir until dissolved. Cover and cool until it begins to congeal.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper in a large bowl.
Add vegetables and toss to mix.

title: broccoli sausage casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased 12 x 15-inch glass casserole dish.
Bake, covered, for 25 minutes at 350°.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: good for what ails you(2 different recipes)
directions: Mix; drink 2 ounces daily.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well and roll in 1-inch balls.	Chill 2 hours or longer.
Melt semi-sweet chocolate, bitter chocolate and paraffin wax.
Dip balls in mixture and refrigerate.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Combine egg white and water.
Add nuts, stir to coat nuts; set aside.
In a bag, combine remaining dry ingredients.
Add pecans and shake to coat thoroughly.
Spread on greased baking sheet. Bake at 275° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven, use a fork to flip nuts onto waxed paper to cool.
Store in a tightly sealed container.
Yields 4 cups.

title: ziti chicken salad
directions: Combine vinegar and oil and coat cooked ziti.
Add other ingredients and toss.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Turn oven onto 350°.
Grease baking dish.
Boil sweet potatoes until tender.
Mash up good.
Add all ingredients.
Bake in oven dish for 45 minutes.

title: chicken mozzarella(makes 2 to 4  servings)
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook for 3 to 4 minutes on each side or until golden brown; drain. Pour tomatoes and juice over chicken. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium-low; cover.
Cook for 20 to 25 minutes or until chicken is tender. Place cheese over chicken and tomatoes; cover. Cook for 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese is melted. Serve over pasta or rice.

title: boiling oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, cocoa, margarine and vanilla well.
Boil 1 minute.
Add peanut butter and/or coconut.
Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal.
Stir well.
Drop on wax paper.

title: company potatoes
directions: Squeeze all the moisture from the hash browns.
Mix together margarine, soup, sour cream and onions.
In a large glass baking dish (13 x 9-inch), place half the potatoes and half the soup mix. Salt and pepper this and sprinkle with half the cheese.
Put on the remaining potatoes and repeat layers.
Last, top with cheese. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: stuffed jumbo shells
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef.
Drain off grease.
Add chili sauce, spaghetti sauce, basil, oregano, parsley flakes and sugar. Heat large pot of water and 1 teaspoon salt.
When boiling, add jumbo shells.
Cook as package directs.
Meanwhile, in large bowl, add Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella, Parmesan cheese and egg and mix thoroughly.
Drain jumbo shells in cold water.
Stuff jumbo shells with the cheese mixture.

In the bottom of pan, put thin layer of meat and sauce mixture, then layer stuffed shells on top of sauce. When all noodles are stuffed and in the pan, pour the rest of the sauce over top of pasta shells.
Then spread shredded Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until cheese is browned.
Serve with hot French bread or garlic toast.

title: chocolate scotcheroos
directions: Place corn syrup and sugar into large saucepan. Cook over medium heat until sugar dissolves and mixture begins to boil. Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter. Add Rice Krispies cereal and stir until well coated. Press mixture into a 13 x 9-inch pan coated with cooking spray. Set aside. Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips over low heat, stirring constantly. Spread evenly over cereal mixture. Let stand until firm and cut into bars when cool.

title: jan hagle
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch).
Mix sugar, oleo and egg yolk.
Mix in flour and cinnamon.
Press into pan.
Beat egg white with water until foamy. Brush over dough.
Sprinkle with nuts.
(Press nuts lightly into dough before baking.)
Bake until lightly brown, 20 to 25 minutes. Immediately cut into squares about 3 x 1-inch.
Makes 50 cookies.

title: beef roundup
directions: Mix well and form into rolls; wrap with cabbage leaf.
Secure with a toothpick.
Place rolls in pan and add tomatoes.
Cook in a 350° oven for an hour or until tender.

title: anne's cheese dip
directions: Mix together.
Chill and serve with vegetable or crackers.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Blend powdered sugar and cocoa in mixing bowl.
Without stirring, add
milk and butter.
Cook in microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Remove bowl and stir just to mix ingredients.
Add vanilla
and
nuts
and stir until blended.
Pour into greased container
and place in freezer for 20 minutes or refrigerator for 1 hour.
Cut and serve.

title: batter for oriental cooking
directions: Mix all in a large bowl until batter is thinner than pancake batter.
Dip whatever is cooked in batter, then drop into hot oil in deep fryer.
Fry until golden brown.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Cook on stovetop until it thickens and boils. Put into 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish.

title: never fail homemade noodles
directions: In a large bowl, mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Make a well in the center.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat with a fork, then fingers until well mixed.
Dough will be stiff.
Roll out on floured surface until very thin.
Let set to dry.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine sauerkraut, celery, pepper, onion, carrots and pimento. Bring to boil oil, sugar, vinegar and salt.
Cool and pour over kraut mixture.
Let set several hours before serving.

title: hot mustard shrimp
directions: In a large bowl combine vinegar, catsup, horseradish, mustard, garlic, salt and pepper.
Blend in oil.
Add shrimp.
Chill, serve in a bowl with toothpicks; garnish with chives.
Serves 6.

title: blender cole slaw
directions: Cut cabbage into 2-inch pieces.
Quarter onion.
Place 1/4 of cabbage in blender.
Cover in water.
Chop and drain.
Repeat with remaining cabbage, onion and carrots.
Mix with remaining ingredients and chill.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: rose's bing cherry salad
directions: Heat juice to boiling.
Pour over both packages of gelatin. Stir, then add 2 cans Coca-Cola.
Chill until slightly thickened. Mix together the cream cheese, celery, fruit and nuts.
Fold into gelatin.
Serves 18 to 20.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix each item as you go along.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Add buttermilk, eggs and oil and mix well.
Place 1 tablespoon shortening in a 10-inch cast-iron skillet in a 450° oven for 3 to 4 minutes or until hot.
Tilt pan evenly to distribute shortening.
Pour batter into skillet.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and crumble the cornmeal into a large bowl.
Cook celery and onion in 1/4 cup broth in a skillet until tender.
Add celery mixture, remaining broth and remaining ingredients to cornbread crumbs.
Mix well.
Spoon into a large greased baking dish.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: four cheese fettucine
directions: Cook fettucine according to package; drain and set aside. Over medium-low heat melt butter; stir in milk and cheese.
Stir together cheese mixture, parsley and pepper with fettucine.
Serve sprinkled with additional grated Romano cheese.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Bake cake according to box directions as to size of pan and temperature for baking.
Punch holes in cake while it is still hot with a fork.
Dribble Eagle Brand milk over cake, then dribble 1/2 can cream of coconut over cake.
Freeze other half of cream of coconut for later use.
Cool cake thoroughly.
Cover top with Cool Whip, then spread with coconut.
This can be baked in an oblong pan.

title: white bean chili
directions: Soak beans overnight in cold water.
Wash chicken and cover with 1/2 of spice mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Heat oil in skillet.
Saute onions, chilies and garlic for 1 minute.
Drain beans and add beans and stock to pot.
Add sauteed vegetables, spice mixture and beer.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for about 2 hours or until beans are tender.
Dice chicken into quarter size pieces.
Add to stock and simmer a little longer.

title: almond chocolate covered toffee
directions: Lightly grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Boil sugar, butter, water and corn syrup over medium heat without stirring until candy thermometer equals 300° to 310° (or drop small amounts of candy into ice water.
When candy forms a brittle mass that snaps when pressed, it is ready.)
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour mixture into pan.
Wait 2 minutes, then sprinkle evenly with chocolate chips.
When chips turn shiny, spread over toffee. Sprinkle almonds over top, pressing them gently into chocolate. Refrigerate candy until cold.
Break into bite-size pieces.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 2 1/4 pounds.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown chops lightly in hot skillet.
Remove to baking pan. Pour fat from skillet, leaving about 1 tablespoon in pan.
Add flour and onion soup mix.
Blend in water.
Pour over chops. Cover with foil; bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover, bake 30 to 40 minutes longer or until tender.

title: cream cheese mint
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar together.
Start with 4 drops flavoring, then add color.
Knead until pie dough consistency. Take small pinch and roll into ball in granulated sugar.
Press into mold.
Remove excess and unmold at once onto waxed paper. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: broiled crab meltaways
directions: Slice muffins in half, then cut each half in fourths.
Arrange on 2 cookie sheets.
Mix remaining ingredients well in small bowl or your mixer on medium speed.
Spread mixture on muffins.
Freeze at least 30 minutes, even if you are going to use the same day. Just before serving, broil until puffy, bubbly and slightly brown, a few minutes.

title: low-fat pasta primavera
directions: Cook linguine until tender.
Meanwhile, spray a large skillet with vegetable spray.
Add mushrooms and 2 tablespoons of the chicken broth.
Cover and cook until tender.
Transfer to a bowl. Spray a skillet again.
Add vegetables and 2 tablespoons chicken broth.
Cover and cook until tender.
Add salt and pepper. Transfer to mushroom bowl.
Add onion to skillet and stir-fry until they start to brown.
Add wine and scrape any browned pieces left. Boil until wine is reduced by half.
Add remaining 1/4 cup chicken broth and remove from heat.
Whisk in sour cream.
Stir in basil and cheese.
Drain pasta and return to pot over low heat, shaking to evaporate excess moisture.
Remove from heat and add sauce and vegetables.
Toss to coat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Makes 6 servings.

title: oven cooked chicken meal
directions: Coat chicken with flour and brown in Dutch oven size pan, using small amount of oil.
Remove chicken and add potatoes and carrots.
Coat well with seasoned salt and little pepper.
Place chicken breasts on top and add more seasoned salt and pepper.
Mix soup and water.
Pour over chicken and cover with lid.
Bake at 250° to 300° for 4 to 5 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: church windows
directions: Melt margarine and chips. Cool just a little. Add marshmallows and nuts. Stir. This does not look like it will stick together. Tear off about 12 to 15 inches of foil. Sprinkle with coconut. Pour mixture onto foil and coconut. Sprinkle a little more coconut on top. Roll and wrap in foil. Put in freezer until it becomes hard enough to slice.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients and stir until well blended.
Knead.
Form into balls and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: broiled tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes in half and scoop out about 1/3 of each half. Chop the pulp.
Mix with cracker crumbs, bacon, worcestershire sauce, soy sauce, salt and pepper to taste.
Stuff each half with the above and top with cheese and cracker crumbs.
Brown under broiler.
Serves 4.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables and drain.
Mix with next 3 ingredients. Place in casserole.
Combine cracker crumbs with margarine and spread over top of vegetables.
Bake in 350°
oven until bubbly (30 to 45 minutes).

title: green bean bake
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
Stir in beans and 1/2 can onions.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Stir once.
Top with remaining onions and bake 5 minutes more.
If using almonds, stir them in before baking.

title: cola chicken
directions: Combine cola and ketchup in skillet.
Salt and pepper chicken and place in skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 1 hour or until tender.
Each serving equals 3 protein and 20 optional calories.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Mix together all ingredients and cover with wax paper.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours for easy handling.
Form into small balls and bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: cinnamon pie
directions: Mix together; roll out as a pie crust.
Spread butter and a layer of sugar and cinnamon on dough.
Roll in small jelly roll and bake at 350° until brown.
Cut in small pieces and eat fast before Penn gets home.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cook raisins and water covered, until tender, about 5 minutes. Stir in mixture of sugar and flour; cook over low heat, stirring constantly until boiling.
Boil one minute.
Remove from heat. Stir in lemon juice (more if desired).

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello, then add other ingredients.
Top with whipped cream (and mayonnaise).

title: crabbies(serves 48)
directions: Blend butter and cheese together.
Sir in remaining ingredients; spread on muffins.
Cut into quarters and freeze on cookie sheet.
Place under broiler until bubbly, about 4 minutes. Can also be stored in plastic bags in freezer for later use.

title: sweet cucumber pickles
directions: Gather enough cucumbers, any size, to fill a gallon size jug. Wash the cucumbers and then stand them up whole in the jug.
Fill the jug full of cucumbers.
Add salt (use plain salt).
Cover the cucumbers with apple cider vinegar.
Tie a cloth over the mouth of the jar and leave for 6 weeks.

At the end of 6 weeks, wash the cucumbers thoroughly in cold water, making sure to rinse them good. Dry the cucumbers with paper towels and then slice the cucumbers into round slices and put them back in the gallon jug.
Put sugar over the top of the cucumbers; this sugar will melt and form a liquid.
Add oil of cloves and cinnamon, both of which can be purchased at the local drug store.
Do not seal the jug.
They will keep all year in the jug.
Just keep them in their liquid so they will stay crisp.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Pastry:
Mix cream cheese, flour, and butter.
Chill about an hour, then shape into small 1-inch balls.
Press into gem muffin tins.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
In
separate bowl, mix flour, cinnamon, salt and baking
soda.
Combine
with apple mixture. Pour into greased, floured 9
x
13-inch
pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bannertown broccoli salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar. Chill the dressing for at least 1 hour before serving.

title: chattanooga beef roast
directions: Brown roast in oil in Dutch oven, turning to coat all sides. Add 4 cups of water and bouillon cubes.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over top.
Simmer 3 1/2 to 4 hours, turning occasionally.
Add more water as needed.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each.
Add buttermilk and beat well.

title: apple-nut bread
directions: Stir together ingredients in order given.
Pour batter into 2 greased 8-inch loaf pans and sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar, mixed with 1 tablespoon melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: skillet fiesta
directions: Brown meat and onion in large skillet; drain.
Dissolve bouillon cube in water.
Mix with tomatoes, corn and chili powder. Add to ground meat and cook for 10 minutes on low heat.
Then bring to boiling point and add bell peppers.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Bring to boiling point again and add rice.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let sit for 5 minutes.
Good served with green beans, Mexican cornbread and slaw.

title: main dish - pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in frying pan for 10 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Layer pork chops and half of the potatoes in baking pan with 2 or 3-inch sides.
Add 1 can of the soup.
Layer the rest of the pork chops and potatoes.
Add the other can of soup and 1 can of water.
Bake in oven for 1 hour.
Serve with salad, green vegie and applesauce.
It's yummy!
Serves 3 to 6.

title: riviera salad
directions: Mix sugar, mustard and vinegar in blender.
Add oil.
Stir in seeds by hand.
Pour over salad greens.
Add sliced strawberries and chopped walnuts.

title: dill pickles
directions: Pour mixture over cucumbers and seal and let set for 6 weeks.

title: cottage cheese dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Heat cheese to lukewarm; mix with yeast, sugar, eggs, soda and salt.
Stir in flour to make a soft dough.
Place in greased bowl.
Turn to grease all sides of dough. Let rise in oven (place pan of hot water on rack under bowl) about 1 1/2 hours, until doubled.
Punch dough down, pinch in half and work each half into 12 pieces.
Roll each piece in flour. Place on greased pan; let rise again until doubled.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Brush with butter and serve warm.

title: fat-free devil's food cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together; blend well.
Bake in greased (nonstick spray) 9 x 13-inch baking dish at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with frozen yogurt or hot fudge topping.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Cream shortening and brown sugar in bowl until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Reserve 1/4 cup flour.
Sift remaining flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture; mix well.
Coat pecans with reserved flour.
Stir into mixture.
Press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: oyster stew
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bring to a boil (do not scorch).
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Mix pudding and Cool Whip together.
Add pineapple with juice; mix well.
Add marshmallows and mix well.
Chill.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken in oil in a large frypan.
Drain excess oil. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 45 to 50 minutes until tender.
If desired, serve chicken pieces with sauce over rice or spaghetti.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cutout christmas cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Roll on floured board.
Cut out your cookies.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes. This dough may be used for raisin filled cookies or any filled cookies.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix the above and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: mounds candy
directions: Combine milk, powdered sugar, coconut, nuts and melted butter. Mix well.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
In a double boiler melt chocolate chips and paraffin.
Roll the coconut mixture into 1 1/2 inch balls.
Dip into chocolate and place on Wax paper lined cookie sheet.
Let set.
Serve.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and hot water.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well and refrigerate until jelled.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugars and vanilla until fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt gradually to creamed mixture.
Beat well; add chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: church window cookies
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butter. Let cool.
Add marshmallows and nuts.

title: pizza meat loaf
directions: Mix altogether, except cheese, in 2-quart bowl.
Put in 9-inch square baking dish.
Bake at 300° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Then top with grated cheese.
Let cheese melt and serve.

title: broccoli-rice-cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain well.
Cook rice in 1 1/2 cups water. Saute onion in melted margarine.
Add soup and 1 scant soup can of water; add broccoli, cheese and rice.
Mix thoroughly; put in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: deluxe fajita nachos
directions: In medium skillet, combine chicken, spices and seasonings for fajitas and water; blend well.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 3 minutes.

title: quick lasagne
directions: Brown meat with onion and spices; drain grease.
Add tomato sauce and small amount of water.
Reduce heat; simmer 20 minutes. In greased 9 x 13-inch pan place one-half meat mixture on bottom; add layer of noodles.
Add cottage cheese; sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Place remaining beef on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
During last 10 minutes put Mozzarella cheese on top to melt.

title: hungarian pastry
directions: Blend dry ingredients together; cut in margarine.
Beat eggs and add vanilla; add to dry mixture and blend well.
Form ball and cut in
half.
Pat	half
into long cake pan and roll out second half
and cut into strips to make woven top.
Dough handles better when
slightly
cooled.
(You may use 2 cans of prepared pie filling
or
your
favorite
recipe for the fruit filling.) Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: broccoli deluxe(microwave)
directions: Cook frozen broccoli in microwave for 5 to 6 minutes.
Let stand 4 to 5 minutes and drain.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Butter 13 x 9-inch pan.
Crush ice cream wafers and put 3/4 of them in bottom of pan.
Pat down.
Cream together butter and powdered sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Beat.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add to mixture.
Mix well.
Spread over wafers.
Put a layer of nuts on top, then add your strawberries.
Whip the whipping cream; spread on top, then sprinkle with the rest of your crushed wafers.
Chill.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Pour pineapple and juice into greased casserole dish.
Mix sugar and flour.
Pour over pineapple.
Top with cheese and Ritz cracker crumbs.
Pour melted margarine on top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat together sugar, oil and eggs until fluffy.
On slow speed, add dry ingredients, then vanilla, apples and pecans.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake at 275° for 30 minutes and at 300° for 1 hour.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet, brown chops and drain on paper towel.
In buttered baking dish, arrange potatoes, chops and mushrooms.
In small bowl, combine soup mixture and water.
Pour over meat.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: guiltless chocolate pie
directions: Prepare ready bake crust as directed on instructions (substituting egg white for egg).
Prepare pudding mix as directed on box.
Pour pudding in pie shell.
Spread Cool Whip on top. Chill for 1 hour.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix ingredients and put into pie shells.
Refrigerate.

title: barbecued meat balls
directions: Break bread into small pieces and soak in milk.
Combine other ingredients.
Form into marble size balls.
Pour your favorite barbecue sauce over.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Place toothpicks before serving.
Serve warm.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Heat juice from pineapple and cherries.
Dissolve cherries in this.
Pour in Coke and pre-jell.
Add remaining ingredients and return to refrigerator.

title: california shrimp curry
directions: In medium saucepan, saute green onion, celery, curry powder and shrimp in butter for 2 to 3 minutes. Stir in flour.
Off heat, add milk.
Cook, stirring over low heat until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in lemon juice and seasoned salt.
Serve over cooked rice.
Serves 4.
May be doubled.

title: marinated salad
directions: Cut up all vegetables.
Combine in large container with tight lid.
Mix together all remaining ingredients with a wire whisk. Pour marinade over vegetables; toss.
Cover and chill at least 3 hours.
Lasts several days.

title: mushroom appetizer
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients and refrigerate. When ready to serve, spread on party rye bread.
Put under broiler long enough to melt cheese.
This topping is enough to cover 1 loaf of party rye or cocktail pumpernickel bread.

title: butterscotch cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees (for glass dish 325 degrees). In medium sauce pan, melt butterscotch morsels and butter. Stir in graham cracker crumbs and nuts.

title: sunshine preserves
directions: Combine sugar and honey.
Bring slowly to boil.
Add the pitted cherries.
Cook 12 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Place kettle in greased shallow pan.
Cover with glass lid and allow to stand in sunshine one day or longer.
Seal in hot, sterile jars.

title: bread pudding with vanilla sauce
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; stir in butter and whipping cream. Gently stir in bread and raisins. Pour into lightly greased 2-quart deep baking dish. Bake at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes, shielding with aluminum foil after 30 minutes to prevent too much browning. Let stand 10 minutes before serving warm with Vanilla Sauce (recipe follows).

title: cookies 'n cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour pans.
In large bowl combine all but cookies and beat at low speed until moistened, then on high for 2 minutes.
Gently fold in crushed cookies.
Pour into prepared pans and bake until tests done, 25 to 35 minutes. Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool completely and frost.

title: berry-orange cake
directions: Prepare cake mix per box instructions.
Bake and cool. Combine the cream cheese, lemon juice and Cool Whip until folded smoothly together.
Cover first cake layer with the cream cheese mixture, then evenly place prepared blueberries.
Stack second layer; cover with cream cheese mixture, then evenly top cake with prepared strawberries.

title: chicken salad
directions: Stir first 7 ingredients with wooden spoon.
Add chicken and mix (as with a salad - lifting up and down).
Place in refrigerator at least 1 hour or longer so all seasonings are absorbed.
Serve on lettuce or toast.

title: world's best brownies
directions: Blended oil, sugar and vanilla in large mixing bowl. Add eggs, beat well with spoon. Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt; blend gradually into egg mix. Stir in nuts (optional). Spread in greased nine inch pan. Bake 350 degrees for 20-25 minutes or until brownie begins to pull away from edges of pan. Cool, cut into squares.

title: stouffer's oatmeal macaroons
directions: Melt butter in a 2-quart pan.
Stir in oats and brown lightly over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Set aside and cool.
Blend flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into cooled oats.
Blend egg, vanilla and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful 3-inches apart onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken tarragon
directions: Dredge chicken in flour to coat completely.
Discard flour not used.
Melt butter and oil in frying pan.
Brown chicken on both sides and remove.
In the same pan, saute leeks and carrots.
Stir in wine.
Add bouillon and tarragon.
Return chicken to pan and cover.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken and cook uncovered for 15 minutes.
Remove chicken.
Stir in sour cream; heat and pour over chicken.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and spread on round platter (at least 12-inches in diameter).
Arrange remaining ingredients on top of sour cream mixture in order given.
Arrange Doritos chips around edge of platter and serve with dip.

title: barbecue
directions: Do not use salt.
The soup is salty enough.

title: tomato onion salad
directions: Combine garlic, salt and sugar substitute into a small bowl. Make salad dressing with water only.
Add vinegar and parsley. Pour over tomatoes and onion.
Chill.
This salad can be made and placed in Thermos container and taken to any picnic.

title: angel cookies
directions: Cream butter, lard and sugar together; add eggs and mix thoroughly.
Add
vanilla.
Sift
flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt together;
add
to
cream
mixture.
Stir in nuts and chill. Shape in
balls
the
size
of
a walnut.
Dip tops in sugar.
Put 2
inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° about 15 minutes.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: chicken with mustard sauce
directions: Clean chicken; place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Saute garlic, onion, celery and mushrooms in oil.
When tender, add broth, wine and mustard.
Thicken with cornstarch.
Pour over chicken.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: cranberry whip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let stand for 2 hours before serving.

title: apricot cream
directions: Drain and chop cooked apricots, reserving syrup.
Grate 1 teaspoon of rind from orange peel and dice orange.
Soften gelatin in cold water.
Heat 3/4 cup apricot syrup, sugar and salt on low heat.
Dissolve gelatin in this mixture.
Add fruits and rind. Cool until slightly thickened.
Whip the cream and fold into fruit mixture.
Cool until firm.
Makes 4 servings.

title: rye bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Place in a large bowl. Mix rest of ingredients and add enough white flour to make a stiff dough.
Bake about 375° to 400° until lightly brown.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix well. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar, shortening and eggs. Beat.
Add water and pumpkin. Beat. Add all dry ingredients. Beat thoroughly.
Place into greased and floured bread pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. When toothpick comes out clean, remove and cool.

title: party punch
directions: In a large bowl, combine the strawberries, sugar and 1 bottle of the juice.
Cover and let stand for 1 hour.
Strain the mixture through a fine sieve into a punch bowl, pushing the fruit through with the back of a wooden spoon.
Stir in the lemonade concentrate.
Add the remaining bottle of juice and the sparkling water.

title: magic cookie bar
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish). In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt butter in oven. Sprinkle graham crackers over butter; pour Eagle Brand evenly over crumbs. Top with remaining ingredients. Press down firmly with fork. Bake 25 minutes or until lightly browned; cool. Chill if desired. Cut into bars or diamonds. Store, covered, at room temperature.

title: creamy coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix and bake as directed in 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool 15 minutes.
Make holes down through cake with fork.
Combine milk, sugar and 1/2 cup of coconut in saucepan; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 1 minute.
Spoon over warm cake allow mixture to soak down through holes in cake.
Cool completely. Fold 1/2 cup coconut into whipped topping and spread over cake. Sprinkle with remaining coconut and chill overnight.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix butter in saucepan; mix with 1 package of stuffing mix. Line bottom of 2 casserole dishes.
Place diced chicken on top of stuffing mix.
Mix both cans of soup with the 2 cups of chicken broth; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle 1/2 package of stuffing mix over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Can be frozen and baked later.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles (about 20 minutes).
Brown meat; add onions and cook until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, water, garlic and seasonings.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Place in baking dish a layer of noodles, meat sauce and cheese.
Repeat layers and finish with lots of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted good.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Melt 1 stick butter.
Mix with the graham cracker crumbs and pat on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: special "k" roast
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in loaf pan and let bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add remaining spices.
Add tomato paste and water.
Stir well.
Allow to simmer for at least 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
If sauce becomes thick, add a little water.

title: easy no-bake pudding cookies
directions: Stir first 3 ingredients together in saucepan and bring to a rolling
boil on medium heat.
Boil about 3 minutes, then remove from heat.
Stir in the next 3 ingredients.
Mix well and let stand for 5 minutes.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful on waxed paper. Let cool and store in refrigerator.

title: aunt kate's cream puffs
directions: Combine water and butter; bring to a boil.
Add flour, all at once and beat well.
Add 4 eggs, one at a time, beat well between each addition.
Drop batter by spoonful onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: pennsylvania dutch salad dressing
directions: Boil ingredients together until thickened.
Use half dressing and half mayonnaise for potato or macaroni salad.

title: super quick chicken noodle casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Serves 8.

title: heavenly devil's food cake
directions: Mix and bake as directed on package.
Cool.

title: brown bread
directions: Cut shortening into dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients; beat thoroughly.
Pour into 2 bread pans (9 x 5-inch).
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: baked chili rellenos
directions: In a greased casserole layer green chilies with grated cheese. Fold beaten egg yolks into stiffly beaten egg whites.
Add green onion and garlic powder.
Mix together flour, baking powder and milk.
Pour all over chilies.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Thaw and press all water from spinach.
Mix spinach, onion soup mix and sour cream.
Put into a casserole dish and bake, uncovered, at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until done.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Cream together first 2 ingredients.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Mix dry ingredients in separate bowl.
Blend well and add alternately with zucchini.
Add nuts.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut.

title: bean and macaroni soup
directions: In oil saute onion, pepper and garlic 5 minutes.
Add tomato sauce.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add a little water as needed.
Stir frequently.
Add drained beans, parsley, green onion and liquid (bean and water).
Season to taste.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Stir in cooked macaroni and simmer 5 more minutes.
(Cook macaroni about 8 minutes.)
Sprinkle with bacon.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Put first 3 items into bowl.
Stir together vinegar, mayonnaise and sugar.
Pour over broccoli mixture and toss.
Add raisins, bacon bits and sunflower seeds just before serving.
Add tomatoes for color.

title: andrews chocolate pie
directions: Use an 8-inch glass or porcelain pie plate.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
It makes its own crust.
Top with whipped cream.
Serves 8.

title: surprise muffins
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 8 muffin cups.
Unroll rolls into 8 triangles.
Flatten each and spread with butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Put a marshmallow at the short side of each triangle.
Roll crescent roll around marshmallow.
Pinch edges shut, tightly!
Place rolls in muffin cups.
Spread remaining butter on top.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: easy cheesy taters
directions: Stir together; bake in 9 x 13-inch pan, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: vanilla wafer jello salad
directions: Crumble vanilla wafers in bottom of oblong rectangular pan. Soften cream cheese.
Mix softened cream cheese with
Cool Whip. Spread Cool Whip mixture over vanilla wafers, sealing edges of pan.
Prepare Jell-O following package directions.
Refrigerate Jell-O until slightly thickened.
Add fruit cocktail, bananas and pecans.
Pour Jell-O mixture into rectangular pan over Cool Whip mixture.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: peanut butter milk shake
directions: Mix ingredients well with mixer or in bender.
Pour in glass and drink up.

title: liver and onion
directions: Cut liver into 3-inch squares.
Season with salt and pepper. Roll in flour and pan-fry in shortening.
Fry until golden brown on both sides.
Turn only 1 time.
Remove liver from skillet and fry onion in drippings, stirring constantly.
Return liver to skillet and add water.
Cover with tight fitting lid and cook for approximately 5 minutes.
Liver will become tough if cooked too long.
Serves 5.

title: mom's macaroni and shrimp salad
directions: 1. Hard boil eggs and grate fine.
2. Grate carrots fine, chop green onions fine, grate sweet
pickles and celery fine. 3. Cook macaroni by package directions (I use Elbow
macaroni). 4. Add all ingredients into mixing bowl and toss.
5. Season with pepper and let chill (Tastes better with
time).

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Blend cream cheese and sour cream together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread on tortillas thinly.
Roll each tortilla. Place on cookie sheet.
Cover with Saran Wrap and chill overnight. Slice 1/2-inch thick.
Arrange on platter.
(During Christmas, add red pimentos and arrange in shape of a tree.)
I usually make half of this amount.

title: brie appetizer
directions: Pour preserves on top of Brie and chopped onions.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Serve with crackers.

title: pierogies
directions: Put flour and salt in bowl.
Melt butter in hot water.
Add 2 eggs and melted butter to flour.
Mix.
Let dough rest 10 minutes before rolling.

title: banana cake or bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Bake in loaf pan (8 x 11 x 3-inch).
Double for two loaves.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in small pan (salted) until tender.
In another pan, saute onions in oleo.
Add bouillon cubes.
Add flour making a roux; stir.
Add milk, stirring constantly, until the sauce starts to thicken.
Add potatoes and the water they are in to milk mixture.
Stir until well mixed.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: broccoli and green bean casserole
directions: Combine
broccoli
and	beans
in large casserole dish. Combine soup, mayonnaise, salt, pepper, cheese, onion and eggs and mix
well.
Pour
over vegetables.
Combine margarine and cracker crumbs and sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes
servings.
I make it into 2 small casserole dishes and cook one and freeze one.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash with onion and drain.
Salt and pepper to taste. Combine in saucepan the soup, butter and milk.
When melted, add squash and pour into baking dish.
Top with cheese and bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: blondies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spread in a 9 x 11-inch pan. Sprinkle chocolate and butterscotch bits on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Allow to cool before cutting into squares. Will be soft in middle.

title: chicken in pastry
directions: Place each chicken breast half between 2 sheets of waxed paper.
Flatten chicken to 1/4-inch thickness, using a meat mallet or rolling pin.
Set aside.

title: mem boutin's marble date swirl cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook on stove top for 12 minutes. Chill.

title: guacamole supreme
directions: Mash and mix thoroughly.
Use an avocado pit in center to keep guacamole from turning dark.
Makes 1 to 1 1/2 cups.

title: texas rice bake
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add olives, onion, celery, green pepper and rice and saute together.
Add tomatoes, water and seasonings and bring to a full boil.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole dish and bake at 350°, covered, for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: great grandma's soft molasses cookies
directions: Cream in order given; sift flour and cinnamon.
Add to creamed mixture.
Shape into walnut sized balls and dip tops in sugar. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: plum upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Measure butter into a 9-inch iron skillet or an 8-inch square pan.
Slide into oven long enough to melt.
Stir brown sugar into butter.
Arrange plums; set aside.

title: patsy's green beans
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Bake in a 400° oven for 45 minutes or 15 minutes on High in microwave.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Put vinegar and sugar on stove and let them come to a boil. Then scald the peaches in this solution.
The peaches should stay in long enough to get hot through and through and until they can be pricked with a fork, but should not be allowed to shrivel.
Place in sterilized fruit jars and seal.

title: beef cheese ball
directions: Sprinkle a little seasoned salt over cream cheese.
Mix all ingredients together well and shape into a ball or log.
Roll in chopped pecans and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Make gelatin according to directions on box, except use the pineapple juice instead of water.
Chill until thickened.
Combine remaining ingredients and blend by hand.
Add to thickened gelatin and mix well.
Chill until firm.
If the mixture is somewhat sour from the orange, add sugar to taste.

title: cherry blossom mold
directions: If using canned cherries, be sure to use the cherry syrup in the liquid.
You'll get a richer color and flavor plus requests for seconds.

title: egg custard
directions: Preheat oven to 415°.
Mix eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla. Pour into scalded milk and stir well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake about 20 minutes longer or until custard is set.
Test with a knife an inch or so from the center of the pie.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with bagel chips, veggies, bread, etc.
Excellent!

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Pack mixed cucumbers, onion and peppers in a large jar.
I use 1/2 gallon.
Heat vinegar, sugar, salt and seed to boiling.
Pour over vegetables.
Keep in refrigerator.
Keeps 4 months.

title: dry steak rub
directions: Mix well. Rub into your favorite steak on both sides before cooking, then grill as you normally would. Makes enough for two steaks.

title: fried apple pies
directions: Take cooked apples and sweeten and season with cinnamon and allspice.
Beat 1 egg and set aside.
Take biscuits (I use 1869 store bought biscuits).
Roll out biscuits.
Take clean paint brush and brush on egg around the edge of dough.
Use 1 or 2 large tablespoons apples.
Put on one side of dough; fold the dough over and press edges together with finger.
Take fork and press edges together more firmly.
Put Wesson oil in frypan.
Put pies in skillet.
Cook on 350° until pie is golden brown.
Turn the pie and repeat on the other side.

title: microwave chicken broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli in flat casserole dish 8 minutes in microwave. Then layer on top, chicken, sliced cheese, soup and onion rings. Cover with Saran Wrap.
Microwave 12 minutes on High.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl and add the mayonnaise; mix well.
Chill.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Keep corn warm in a slow 300° oven.
Stir and cook sugar, corn syrup, water, butter and salt until sugar is dissolved.
Continue cooking without stirring until syrup forms a brittle ball or to 270°.
Add vanilla.
Pour syrup slowly over corn.
Mix well. Grease hands and shape into balls.
Makes 12 medium size balls.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Dust chicken lightly in flour.
Heat oil in skillet.
Quickly saute chicken until golden.
Transfer slices to casserole or serving dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Saute pecans in oleo, stirring constantly until toasted (about 5 minutes); set aside to cool.
Mix Milnot, vanilla pudding and sugar; mix well.
Pour into freeze can, finish filling can to about 3/4 full with milk; add vanilla.
Freeze about 10 minutes, add pecans, mix and finish freezing.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Cover bottom of salad bowl with lettuce.
Layer the next 4 ingredients, then spread a thin layer of Miracle Whip on peas. Sprinkle a small amount of sugar onto Miracle Whip.
Add Cheddar cheese; finish with bacon, cut into bits, on top.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
Preparation time:
20 minutes.

title: louise's cherry pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and eggs together.
Mix well.
Add flour and whipping cream to mixture, then add extract.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour, then on 300° for 30 minutes.
Turn oven off and let set for 5 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine ingredients in a casserole dish.

title: jello dessert
directions: Combine all ingredients together; mix well.
Put in dish. Sprinkle with pecans.
Put red or green cherries on top.

title: irish-american lamb stew
directions: Brown lamb in margarine in large Dutch oven or heavy saucepan with tight fitting cover.
Add water, salt, pepper and thyme. Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Skim off excess fat.
Add potatoes and onions.
Simmer, covered, 30 minutes.
Add peas and mushrooms. Simmer, covered, 15 minutes or until lamb and vegetables are tender.
Blend cream into flour.
Stir into bubbling stew and boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: red cucumber rings
directions: Peel, seed and slice cucumbers into rings.
Soak in 1 cup lime and 1 gallon of water for 24 hours.
Rinse and soak, covered with ice water, for 3 hours.
Mix 1 cup vinegar, 2 ounces red food coloring, 1 tablespoon alum and water to cover.
Pour over cucumbers and simmer 2 hours.
Pour off liquid.
Bring to boil 2 cups vinegar, 2 cups water, 5 pounds sugar, 8 cinnamon sticks and a package of Red Hots.
Pour over cucumbers and let stand 24 hours. Drain, saving liquid.
Pack cukes in jars while bringing liquid to boil, then pour liquid over cucumbers in jars and seal.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak bread in milk five minutes; add butter, salt and sugar. Pour slowly over eggs; add vanilla and mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake in pan of hot water in moderate oven at 350° until firm, about 50 minutes.
One-half cup of raisins may be used if desired.
It may be served warm with Lemon Sauce if desired. Sprinkle nutmeg on top.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix pretzels, 2 tablespoons of sugar and margarine.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 7 minutes at 400°.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and 3 tablespoons sugar.
With pastry blender, cut in shortening until like coarse corn meal. With a fork stir in combined egg and milk.
Spread dough in a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
On top, arrange apple slices, slightly overlapping in parallel rows, with pointed edges down.
Sprinkle with combined cinnamon, nutmeg, 3 tablespoons sugar and butter.
Bake 35 minutes at 400° or until apples are tender.
Beat jelly with water to make syrup.
Brush over fruit when done.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours before serving.
Serve with a variety of raw vegetables.
Also excellent as a topping on baked potato.

title: cheese filled shells
directions: Cook jumbo shells according to package.
Combine cheeses, eggs, parsley, oregano, salt and pepper.
Fill each shell with about 2 tablespoons of cheese mixture.
Spread a thin layer of sauce on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Place shells, open side down, in a single layer.
Cover with remaining sauce.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: cucumber soup
directions: Blend in blender and serve.

title: layered green salad
directions: In 9 x 13 glass dish, tear lettuce into bite-size (probably 6 to 8 cups). Fill dish at least 1/2 full. Sprinkle vegetables over lettuce. Mix 1 cup mayonnaise and 1 cup sour cream. Spread over salad. Sprinkle generously with shredded Cheddar cheese and 2 medium tomatoes (cut into small dices). Cover with plastic wrap. May be prepared the night before. When ready to serve, crumble crisp bacon, not bacon bits, over salad. Also good with small shrimp sprinkled over. (Do not use cukes.)

title: brewsaugh's baked fish
directions: Brush fish with oil.
Roll in mixture of cornmeal, salt, pepper and paprika.
Place fish on a foil lined cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
For added flavor, squeeze fresh lemon over fish.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix corn bread as directed on package.
Add corn, pour 1/2 of corn bread mix in hot, greased pan.
Add layer of meat, onion and cheese.
Add other half of corn bread mix.
Bake in 425° oven.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage in small wedges and cover with water. Cook until tender. Add corned beef, salt and pepper. Simmer 5 minutes.

title: fluffy potato casserole
directions: Season mashed potatoes with salt and pepper.
Add enough hot milk to whip lightly.
Spread into 1 1/2-quart dish.
Blend cheese into whipped cream and pour over potatoes.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: seafood tartlets
directions: Roll each bread slice to 1/4-inch thickness; cut with a 2 1/2 inch daisy shaped cutter.
Lightly brush each side of bread with melted margarine.
Place in miniature tart shells.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
Rinse shrimp; let stand in ice water 20 minutes.
Drain well.
Combine shrimp and next five ingredients; stir well.
Spoon shrimp mixture evenly into tart shells; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until bubbly.
Garnish with parsley sprigs, if desired. Yields 22.

title: almond brickle cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter. Add egg. Add all dry ingredients. Add vanilla. Mix well. Place onto cookie sheet in 1-inch balls. Take a glass and place bottom of glass into a small amount of sugar. Press cookie flat with glass. Bake 8 to 11 minutes in 350° oven.

title: taco bean dip(appetizer or can be used as a main dish.)
directions: Brown the ground beef and onion in a skillet; add the rest of the ingredients except cheese.
Heat through; transfer to a casserole type dish.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.

title: chocolate chiffon pie
directions: Soften gelatin in the 1/4 cup cold water.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon-colored.
Gradually beat in the 1/3 cup sugar; add salt and vanilla.
Combine chocolate and the 1/2 cup water.
Stir over low heat until blended.
Add softened gelatin and stir to dissolve.
Immediately beat chocolate mixture into beaten egg yolks.
Chill until mixture is partially set.

title: potato cake
directions: Mix by hand.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Combine all dry ingredients.
Mix potatoes and milk.
Mix dry ingredients into butter mixture alternately with potato mixture.
Add nuts last.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onions.
Then drain.
Add tomato, jalapeno relish and cheese.
Cook on low heat until cheese is melted (crock-pot works well).
Serve over chips.

title: "not" fried ice cream
directions: Put cereal, coconut, pecans and oleo in a long shallow pan and bake at 300° for 30 minutes until toasted, stirring occasionally. Remove from oven. Add brown sugar and stir. Place half in 13 x 9 pan evenly. Add 1-inch thick slices of softened ice cream and other half of mixture. Pat down and freeze.

title: mexican chicken dish
directions: Saute green chilies and onion in oil. Add other ingredients (except cheese) and simmer for 45 minutes. Add water if needed. Pour over tortilla chips and add shredded cheese on top.

title: avocado rye rounds
directions: Put cottage cheese and avocados into electric blender and blend until smooth.
Blend in onion, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco.
Stir in chicken and celery.
Chill several hours or overnight.
To serve, spread about 1 tablespoon mixture on each rye toast slice.
Garnish with pimento.
Makes about 2 dozen appetizers.

title: whipped cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries; add sugar, pineapple and marshmallows.
Mix well, refrigerate several hours or overnight, then fold in whipped cream.
Add nuts.
Chill 4 to 5 hours.

title: scalloped cheese potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients in order up to pepper.
Put in 13x9 buttered pan.
Spread evenly.
Sprinkle with Ritz Crackers.
Bake 2 hours at 350 until potatoes are cooked.

title: taquito salad
directions: Cook taquitos.
Drain and rinse beans while taquitos are cooking.
Warm corn.
Cut taquitos into 1 inch pieces.
Mix taquitos, tomatoes, corn, onions and cucumbers into large bowl. Add lime juice and taco sauce over top.
Mix well and eat.

title: five-layer taco dip
directions: Combine beans and 2 tablespoons of dressing.
Combine remaining dressing and sour cream.
Mix well.
In a 9-inch pie plate, layer bean mixture, sour cream mixture, tomatoes, olives and cheese; cover.
Chill.
Serve with tortilla or corn chips.

title: peanut butter fondant
directions: Combine peanut butter, milk and powdered sugar.
Mix with hands.
If too stiff, add a little more milk.
Put more powdered sugar on board.
Put mixture out and knead.
Shape in a roll and cool in refrigerator.
Shape into balls or slice.
Dip in melted Hershey's chocolate.

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Soak apricots in 1/2 cup warm water for 30 minutes.
Beat eggs, sugar and melted margarine.
Add dry ingredients alternately with orange juice.
Add apricots and nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured 5 x 9-inch bread pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: banana surprise
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.
Best after 24 hours.

title: fruit cake filling
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook until thick.
Cool slightly. Put between layers of cake.
Make any chocolate icing and put on top of top layer and sides.

title: peach crumble
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Slice fruit into thin slices and place in dish until about 1/2 to 2/3 full.

Mix together salt, baking powder, flour and sugar. Beat the egg into the dry ingredients. Sprinkle the crumble mixture over the fruit. Sprinkle the entire dish with cinnamon. Cut the butter into 3 pieces and place on the top of the cinnamon at each end and in the center.
Bake for 40 minutes at 400°.
Cool to serve. Will be very juicy.

title: party rye corned beef mini sandwiches
directions: Mix all except party rye together in blender.
Put on buttered bread.
Heat at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Melt margarine in Pyrex dish.
Shake chicken pieces in sack containing Bisquick, paprika and salt.
Place chicken in dish and bake at 400° for 1 hour, maybe less.
Do not cover.
Add drained peach halves last 15 minutes of cooking time.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: In large saucepan fry hamburg, onion, pepper and garlic till hamburg is brown. Add tomato sause, paste and water mix well.
Add sugar, bay leaf, seasonings. Also sprinkle parmesan and romano cheese.
Simmer on low for a day and a half until thick.

title: barbecue meat
directions: Place meat in roasting pan; lay onions on top and pour over the sauce made from remaining ingredients.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours in moderate oven or until brown.
Baked potatoes go well with this.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Press in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan and chill.

title: bubbles
directions: Mix ingredients gently.
Let set overnight.
The next morning blow huge bubbles.

title: savory squash
directions: Cook squash and onion in boiling water 20 minutes. Drain well, pressing between paper towels. Stir together squash mixture, sour cream, salt and pepper. Spoon into a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Top with cheese. Stir together cornflake crumbs and melted butter. Sprinkle over casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine brown sugar, flour and salt. Stir in syrups.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla, butter and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie crust, distributing pecans evenly.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine biscuit mix and brown sugar in large mixing bowl.
Combine butter with mashed sweet potatoes, milk and orange zest.
Add potato mixture to biscuit mix and mix until soft dough forms.

title: chicken in mustard cream sauce
directions: Place chicken breasts between 2 sheets of heavy-duty plastic wrap; flatten to 1/4-inch thickness using a meat mallet or rolling pin.
Sprinkle with pepper and spread one side of chicken breasts evenly with 1 tablespoon mustard.
Cook chicken in oil in a large skillet over medium heat, 10 minutes, turning frequently.
Remove from skillet and keep warm.
Combine whipping cream and remaining ingredients in skillet.
Bring to a boil and cook until mixture thickens.
Spoon sauce over the chicken.
Serves 4.

title: delicious sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix together.
Fill thoroughly greased muffin tins 3/4 full. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: achari chicken
directions: Heat some oil in a pot and add some cumin and mustard seeds. Put in the chicken pieces with garlic and ginger paste, curry leaves, salt and turmeric powder and braise well.
Mix yogurt into the chicken and cook for 10 minutes.

title: shake and bake low-fat potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in bag.
Add dry soup mix.
Shake and place in lightly oiled or sprayed baking dish.
Cover with foil.
Cook 25 minutes, then bake, uncovered, for 10 more minutes.
Serves 4.

title: crock-pot applesauce
directions: Put all ingredients into crock-pot.
Cover; cook on low overnight (8 to 10 hours).
Stir and serve.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate chip brownies
directions: Slice the cookie dough from one of the rolls and place on the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan, pressing down to spread the dough evenly.
With an electric mixer, beat the cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and eggs until well blended.
Spread this over the cookie dough. Cover the mixture with the remaining roll of dough, slicing it as you did the first roll.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Melt margarine and stir in soda.
In a large pan combine the first 3 ingredients.
Bring to a boil and cook 8 to 10 minutes. Add soda mixture while stirring constantly and pour onto a large cookie sheet.
Break into pieces when cool.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove and chop stems from mushrooms.
Saute stems and onion in 3 tablespoons butter.
Mix last 5 ingredients and add mixture to sauteed stems and onions.
Heat 1 minute until mixture jells. Brush mushroom caps with remaining butter.
Fill caps with mixture. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, drain, then mix with mayonnaise, onion, mushroom soup and eggs; pour in a baking dish.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top of this mixture.

title: chicken broccoli
directions: Boil chicken and chop into bite size pieces.
Cook broccoli. Place on 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with layer of chicken.
Combine soup, mayonnaise and curry and spread over chicken to make next layer.
Next layer is grated cheese, then bread crumbs.
Dot bread crumbs with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oven fried fish fillets(serves 6)
directions: Separate fillets carefully.
Combine crumbs and spices in a bowl.
Add oil and blend with fork until thoroughly combined. Press fillets into crumb mixture to coat both sides.
Place on nonstick baking sheet.
Bake 12 minutes at 450°, until fish flakes easily with a fork.
Serves 6.

title: easy bake bars
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Add melted butter; pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chips, coconut and nuts over crust.
Pour milk over top.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar together; set aside. Mix margarine, shortening, water and cocoa in saucepan and allow to come to a boil. Pour over the flour mixture and mix well. Beat buttermilk, eggs, vanilla, salt and soda together. Add to the flour mixture and stir well. Pour into a greased and floured 11 x 11 pan. Bake at 400° about 20 minutes.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Add hot water, then flour.
Stir in potatoes and vanilla.
Beat well.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Bake in 3 greased and floured cake pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: beef and beer
directions: Brown beef well in salad oil and remove from pan.
Add flour, sugar and onions in pan.
Cook until soft and slightly caramelized. Add bay leaves, beer and meat to pan.
Cover and simmer until meat is tender.
Thicken sauce if you like; serve over noodles.

title: south of the border dip
directions: Cook sausage and drain on paper towel.
Mix all ingredients with electric mixer.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve warm with white taco chips such as Doritos.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Chill and serve.

title: tawny pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, sugar, salt, spices and flour in mixing bowl. Add eggs; mix well.
Add evaporated milk, water and vanilla; mix.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 45 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.

title: london broil
directions: Pour dressing over steak. Poke holes with a fork.
Refrigerate and marinate for 8 hours, turn occasionally.

title: simple stroganoff
directions: In a skillet, cook hamburger and onion until beef is browned, stirring to separate meat.
Spoon off fat.
Add beef broth, soup and water.
Cover; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Add uncooked noodles and sour cream.
Simmer for 10 minutes or until noodles are tender, stirring often.
Makes 4 servings.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix together all vegetables.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Chill about 24 hours.

title: lemon-cake pie
directions: Cream together butter, flour and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, lemon juice, rind and milk to the creamed mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into the mixture.
Pour into the unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 45 minutes until set like a custard pie.

title: greek cheese triangles
directions: Mix crumbled Feta and cottage cheese thoroughly.
Add eggs and mix well.
Cut Phyllo into strips about 2-inches wide and 10-inches long.
Line them on a board and brush with melted butter lightly.
Place 1 1/2 teaspoons filling on one end of pastry strip and fold corner over to make a triangle.
Continue folding from side to side in a triangle form until desired size is reached. Proceed until all Phyllo and filling are used.
Place triangles in buttered baking pan side by side and brush tops generously with melted butter.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° until golden brown, about 25 minutes.
Makes approximately 125 pieces.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook in double boiler until thick. Pour mixture into baked pastry shell.
Cover with meringue.

title: 7 cup fruit salad
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Mix well with sour cream.
Add other ingredients.
Let stand overnight for best flavor.

title: pork chops with wild rice
directions: Mix rice, soup and water together and put in 9 x 13-inch pan. Add mushrooms.
Arrange pork chops on top.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and paprika over top.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: sour cream cabbage
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add cabbage and stir over low heat for 15 minutes.
Add salt, sugar and sour cream.
Stir until thoroughly heated, but do not boil.
Serves 4.

title: that something before
directions: Mix margarine, cheese, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco, onion powder, and cayenne pepper with mixer until consistency of frosting.
Spread mixture on bread slices.
Stack by 3's and quarter the stacks.
Sprinkle with dill weed.
Freeze on cookie sheets.
Remove and store in freezer in bags.
Do not defrost until ready to bake.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 60.

title: oven fried chicken nuggets italiano
directions: Cut chicken in bite-size pieces.
Mix with salad dressing. Marinate 1 hour.
Combine bread crumbs and cheese.
Roll chicken in mix or shake in a bag.
Arrange in single layer in pan sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake, uncovered, at 475° about 8 minutes.
Serves 4, 220 calories each.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients in bowl.
In separate bowl, combine eggs and vanilla; add pumpkin.
Combine dry ingredients; mix well with mixer.
Stir in raisins, carrots and pineapple.
Pour into sprayed muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins, 48 calories each.

title: never-fail custard
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar and salt.
Add milk and vanilla flavoring. Pour into 8-inch glass baking dish or 8 individual baking cups.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Set in pan of hot water and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool at room temperature. Serve plain or top with whipped cream.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Mix together the rice, soups and milk.
Place in a large casserole (3-quart size).
Put the chicken on top, skin side down.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Make this 3 hours ahead of time.
Place it in a 250° oven, uncovered, for 3 hours.
Turn the chicken over once.
That's all! Serves 4.

title: sourdough corn fritters
directions: Mix ingredients; let set for 1 hour before frying.
Drop balls of batter about the size of walnut into deep fat; cook until they float and are golden brown.
Turn one time.
Do not put too many into the fat at once.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Mix eggs and milk. Add onion, cheese, flour, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well. Fry in hot buttered pan until brown, about 5 minutes on each side. Makes 8 small pancakes.

title: cake punch
directions: You will need one large punch bowl.

title: bean salad with sausage
directions: Brown sausage, onion and celery.
Drain excess fat.
Add to browned sausage the tomato paste, brown sugar and mustard.
Add drained green beans, yellow beans and lima beans.
Then add kidney beans, chili beans and pork and beans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fluffy frozen peanut butter pie
directions: In top of double boiler over hot water, melt peanut butter chips.
Cool slightly.
In medium mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually add milk, blending well.
Beat in sugar and cooled peanut butter chips until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into prepared crust.
Cover.
Freeze until firm. If desired, decorate with chocolate curls.

title: salad monterey
directions: Combine lettuce, apple, orange and celery; toss lightly. Sprinkle with peanuts, raisins or cereal.
Serve with dressing.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cake
directions: Pour water over oatmeal; let stand 10 minutes.
Add sugars and oleo.
Stir until oleo melts.
Add slightly beaten eggs and then dry ingredients.
Add 1/2 package chocolate chips.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan (fluted pan).
Sprinkle nuts and remaining chocolate chips on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: country apple dessert
directions: Mix the cake mix, 1 egg and margarine.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Pour apple pie filling over first layer.
Mix together brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over pie filling. Mix sour cream, egg and vanilla.
Drizzle over brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: crisp peanut butter snacks
directions: In saucepan, melt butter or margarine.
In a large bowl, combine melted butter or margarine, peanut butter, powdered sugar, cereal and peanuts.
Mix well using hands, if necessary.
Chill for 2 hours.
Shape into small balls, about 1 inch in diameter. Store, covered, in refrigerator.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: scalloped cabbage casserole
directions: Place cabbage in saucepan with 1 1/2 tablespoons of water. Cover and cook over low heat until just wilted.
Lay half the cabbage in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish with half the cheese and cracker crumbs.
Season with salt and pepper.
Repeat layers. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli salad supreme
directions: Combine the first 9 ingredients in container of electric blender and process until smooth.

title: chess bars
directions: Mix cake mix, one egg and melted butter into bowl, then firmly press in lightly greased pan.
Take your bag of chips and put on top of the mix.
Press into mix, then mix cream cheese, 2 eggs, powdered sugar.
Mix very good and pour over the cake mix and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: mavis' fish stew
directions: Fry fish and drain on paper towels.
Put the 1/2 cup of oil, reserved from frying, in bottom of saucepan.
Cook onion until tender.
Add tomato sauce, salt, hot sauce and bouillon.
Cook on low for 10 minutes.
Add fish and simmer for 10 to 15 more minutes.
Serve with rice and black-eyed peas.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Cut each tomato in half.
Place, cut side up, in a shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle cut surface with salt and pepper.
Combine the remaining ingredients.
Spoon a portion on top of each tomato; spread to cover cut surface.
Bake in 400° oven 15 minutes or until topping is lightly puffed and tomatoes are hot.

title: banana bread(very moist and good)
directions: Cream together oil and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add mashed bananas, flour and soda (dissolved in buttermilk).
Last, add vanilla and 1/2 cup nuts, if desired.
Bake in a greased loaf pan in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool partially in pan. Remove and cool completely before slicing.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: caesar salad
directions: Make salad and toss in bacon, adding croutons last.
Add dressing and sprinkle salad with cheese.

title: heavenly rice
directions: Fold rice, pineapple, salt and marshmallows into whipping cream.
Pile lightly into sherbet glasses or dessert dishes. Chill.

title: peach pie supreme
directions: Use lemon juice on sliced peaches.
Line pie plate with pastry.
Fill with sliced peaches.
Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, flour, spices and melted shortening; pour over peaches.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 325° and bake for 40 minutes. A crust will form over the top.

title: fruit smoothie shake
directions: Blend together in blender.
Experiment using your favorite fruits.

title: chicken breasts in sour cream
directions: Wrap chicken breasts in bacon.
Line a greased, flat casserole with strips of dried beef.
Place breasts on beef.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over wrapped chicken breasts and dried beef. Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Very good!

title: lemon bars
directions: Combine 1 cup flour and 1/4 cup sugar. Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Press mixture onto bottom of a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: peach pie
directions: Peel, halve and seed peaches, enough to fill the pie shell, then sprinkle over the pie 2 tablespoons flour, 1 cup sugar or more to suit the taste.
Fill the pan with thick, sweet cream and bake until done.

title: beau monde dip
directions: Blend all ingredients well and serve with potato chips.

title: angel breath dessert(serves 20)
directions: Drain juices from fruit cocktail and pineapple; add enough water to make 4 cups liquid to mix with orange Jell-O.
Stir well. Add fruit cocktail and pineapple.
Put into a container, 14 x 8 x 4-inches deep.
Set in refrigerator until firm.

title: grape salad
directions: Wash and dry grapes. Cream the cream cheese and sour cream. Add sugar, vanilla, brown sugar and pecans. Add grapes and cover with mixture completely.

title: do-ahead fruit salad
directions: Prepare gelatin as directed on package; let cool until syrupy. Stir in remaining ingredients except Cool Whip.
Fold in whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Pour in salad mold or loaf pan.
Refrigerate.

title: jack wax
directions: Boil 1 cup maple syrup over medium heat until it forms a thread when dropped from a spoon.
It may also form a hard ball when dropped in cold water.
Gather a bowl of new snow and pour hot syrup over it to form a "spidery" caramelized confection. It's very sweet.

title: yummy snacks
directions: Mix crackers and oil in a bowl, then shake crackers and dressing in a paper bag. Store in a covered container.

title: beef in burgundy sauce
directions: Slice meat into thin strips; brown in oil.
Remove from pan. Saute onions and carrots until carrots are tender-crisp.
Add mushrooms and cook 2 minutes.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and thyme.
Gradually add broth and wine; return meat to pan.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until meat is tender.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Drain, peel and dice.
Saute bacon and onion together until brown.
Stir in flour; add vinegar, water and spices.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Stir constantly. Remove from heat and pour over potatoes, celery and eggs.
Fold together.
Serve hot or cold.

title: fork cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into small balls; press crosswise with fork.
I use a 3-prong fork.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes, or until done.

title: o'brien potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch rectangular Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle with Italian bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: church cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Stir with spoon.
Pour in greased 13 x 9 pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 - 40 minutes.
Cool.

title: brown sugar chews
directions: Stir together egg, brown sugar and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Then add nuts.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes in well-greased 8-inch square pan at 350°.
Should be soft when taken from oven. Cool in pan and cut in squares.
Makes 25.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Break off stems of 12 to 14 mushrooms and discard.
Brush mushroom caps with butter and place on baking sheet.
Mix together remaining butter with other ingredients. Fill each cap with approximately 1 teaspoon of filling.
Bake 5 minutes and then broil until golden.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix the stuffing, oleo and 1 cup water.
Put 1/2 in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together the chicken, salt, celery, onion and salad dressing; put in pan over stuffing.
Top with remaining stuffing.
Mix the eggs and the milk; pour over everything. Refrigerate overnight.
Remove 1 hour before baking.
Cover with soup and bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Top with Parmesan cheese and bake 10 minutes more.

title: cheese stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Scrub the potatoes and rub oil on the skins.
Bake in 450° preheated oven until done.
Press gently with your fingers to check, about 30 to 45 minutes should do it.
Cut potatoes in half; scoop out shells.
Mix well, then add butter, salt, pepper, milk or sour cream and bacon bits.
When a little cool, fold in cheese cubes.
Pile high in potato shells.
(You can do this in the morning.)
Just before serving, sprinkle with grated cheese and bake in 350° oven for about 25 minutes to heat through thoroughly and melt cheese cubes inside.
Serves 8.

title: meatball nibblers
directions: Mix all together and form into balls (small).
Brown on a cookie sheet in oven or in frying pan on stove top.

title: banana bread(quick bread - lite recipe)
directions: Place walnuts on cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° gas oven 8 to 10 minutes until lightly browned.
Combine buttermilk and soda; set aside.
Combine sugar and oil; mix well.
Stir in bananas. Combine flours; add to banana mixture alternately with egg whites. Add buttermilk mixture; stir just until blended.
Fold in walnuts.
Pour into 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan coated with nonstick vegetable cooking spray.
Bake in 350° gas oven 50 to 60 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool on rack.
Yield: 20 servings.

title: cranberry pudding
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add melted butter and milk.
Mix until well combined.
Stir in cranberries.
Bake in a greased loaf pan at 375° for approximately 1 hour.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar, a little at a time.
Beat until mixture is thick.
Add remaining ingredients.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: seared asparagus with portabella mushrooms
directions: Heat oil with salt and red pepper flakes over high heat in a large skillet.
When very hot, add asparagus and mushrooms.
Cook, shaking often, until tender and asparagus begins to brown. Sprinkle with Parmesan.

title: old fashion chocolate cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Add oil, coffee and milk; mix at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and vanilla (be sure to use pure vanilla).
Beat 2 more minutes. Batter will be thin.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 1 1/2-inch cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool cakes 15 minutes before removing from pans.
Cool on wire racks. Frost with your favorite icing.

title: pat's pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Add vegetables and dressing.
It will usually take at least one whole bottle of dressing.
Serve with toasted pita bread or crackers.

title: easy sausage quiche
directions: Press rolls over lightly buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Cook sausage in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Drain.
Spread over crust.
Pour eggs over sausage.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until set.

title: eagle brand fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Grease pan and line with oiled paper. Pack ingredients with buttered hands.
Bake at 300° in pan of hot water for 1 hour.
Then take out of hot water and bake 15 minutes more.
Leave cake in pan.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, green onions, Worcestershire sauce and Accent. Shape mixture into a round ball. Roll ball in the pressed ham until completely covered. Refrigerate overnight. Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O according to package directions and pour into oblong or rectangular baking dish.
Set until firm.
Combine blueberries and pineapple and pour over Jell-O.

title: baked bean and wiener soup
directions: In large saucepan over medium heat, cook onion, wieners and garlic in margarine until onion is tender.
Stir in flour and mustard.

Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly until blended. Gradually stir in tomato juice, water, Worcestershire sauce and baked beans; cook until slightly thickened, stirring constantly. Simmer uncovered 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Garnish each serving with cheese.
Makes 7 (1 cup) servings.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into 1 to 1 1/2-inch balls. Bake on cookie sheet for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: monkey bread
directions: Melt butter and 1 cup of sugar and set aside.
Mix remaining sugar and cinnamon and set aside.
Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces. Roll biscuits in cinnamon mixture.
Take half of biscuits and put into a greased tube pan.
Pour half of sugar and butter over biscuits.
