Put other half of biscuits in tube pan and pour remaining butter and sugar mixture over all.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken until done (I cook mine in pressure cooker). Remove chicken from bone and set aside.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Cut in shortening until the mixture
resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in buttermilk.
Knead dough gently.

title: honey pecan chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, grapes and pecans.
Set aside.
Stir mayonnaise, sour cream, honey and poppy seed and pepper.
Blend well.
Add to chicken mixture; toss well.
Serve on lettuce leaves or put on croissant buns.

title: world's finest chocolate pie
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients over low heat until well blended. Let mixture cool, then fold in 1 cup of the whipped cream or topping.
Pour into the graham cracker crust and chill well. Cover top with additional whipped cream or topping.

title: potato soup
directions: Dice the potatoes and cook with onion in salted water until soft.
Brown the flour and shortening in a heavy frying pan, stirring well until browned.
Bring the potatoes and water to a boil; then stir in the browned flour and boil until it thickens. Water can be drained from the potatoes and milk may be used instead.

title: persimmon pudding with topping
directions: Preheat oven to 350 - 400 degrees mix butter and sugar. Add eggs and beat well.
Add persimmons and dry ingredients.
Mix well and bake in 9 x 13 inch pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cupid baked alaska
directions: Beat egg whites and salt in medium bowl until softness forms. Add sugar gradually, beating until stiff.
Place cake slices on cookie sheet.
Place one scoop of ice cream on each slice of cake. Spread egg white mixture over ice cream.
Bake at 450° for 4 minutes (ice cream will slightly melt).
Then, after 4 minutes, take out cakes and add raspberries to your desire.

title: potato soup
directions: Cut up potatoes and bring to boil in an uncovered pot of water for 5 minutes.
Drain water.	Add milk, chicken broth, water, onions, butter and celery salt.
Cook on medium heat for 15 minutes.

title: blue cheese ball
directions: Combine Blue cheese, cream cheese and pineapple in bowl; mix well.
Form into ball.
Roll cheese ball in crushed pecans.
Chill until serving time.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix eggs and Pet milk in blender.
Add vanilla, sugar and Eagle Brand milk to blender.
Finish with whole milk.
Fruit may be added.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix the oregano, basil, French dressing and mayonnaise; stir into spaghetti.
Chill overnight.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; rinse and cool pasta.
Put pasta in a large bowl.
Mix the olives, pepperoni, ham or turkey and cheese; pour dressing in and mix well.
Chill salad 1 to 2 hours to mix flavors well.
Stir before serving.
Great with picnics and cookouts.

title: pancakes
directions: Heat the griddle or skillet.
In a large bowl, combine all the ingredients.
Measure 1/4 cup per pancake onto griddle or skillet and cook.
Serve with butter and warm syrup.
Pancakes can be reheated.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Heat oil in pan until hot.
Add 1 tablespoon flour at a time; mix thoroughly.
Add milk; let milk start to boil.
Add white cheese (exclude 12 to 15 slices); let melt.
Add Velveeta, few blocks at a time.
Boil macaroni while mixing all of the other ingredients.
Put macaroni in a 9 x 13-inch pan; pour mixture over it.
Lay cheese slices on top evenly.
Bake at 350° until cheese is browned.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss the ingredients together.
Chill before serving.

title: cornflake candy
directions: Bring sugar and Karo to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter; stir until well mixed.
Add cornflakes.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: old-time egg custard
directions: Scald milk.
Put eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla in blender; blend.
Add milk, blend well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes, then 425° for 10 minutes or until done.

title: neiman-marcus cookies
directions: In bowl, mix butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
In another bowl, mix flour, oatmeal, salt, baking soda and baking powder. Add the 2 bowls together and add chips, candy bar and nuts.
Roll in balls and bake at 375° for 6 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, pepper, onion, cheese, margarine, mushroom soup, chicken soup and sour cream.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with 2 cups crushed Ritz crackers with 1/4 cup melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Make cream mixture of salt, vanilla, milk and flour; set aside.
Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make a paste with cocoa, vinegar and food coloring.
Add to shortening-sugar mixture, then add the cream mixture.
Mix well.
Bake in three layers at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: old-fashioned stack cake
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients well; form stiff dough.
Divide into 6 balls, roll out and press into 8 or 9-inch pans with fingers. Bake at 400° until brown.
Stack cake using apples between layers and on top.

title: zucchini tomato bake
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients until tender.
Add remaining ingredients (except cheese) and simmer approximately 10 minutes or until zucchini is crisp and tender.
Transfer to baking dish. Remove most of the broth; it should be wet, not soupy.
Top with cheese and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: smoky peas and potatoes
directions: Cook whole potatoes in salted water until done.
Drain.
Drain peas.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain.
In saucepan, melt butter. Add flour, salt, pepper, paprika and milk.
Cook until thickened. Add cheese and stir until melted.
Combine potatoes and peas in greased casserole.
Pour on sauce.
Sprinkle crumbled bacon on top.
Bake in oven at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: eggplant sandwiches with gorgonzola cheese and spinach
directions: If desired, trim off and discard the skin of each eggplant round.
Place each round on a flat surface and hold a knife parallel to the surface.
Cut each round in half, splitting each sandwichlike almost but not through to the end.
Leave a small hinge at one end of each round.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: shipwreck casserole
directions: Place in baking dish the ground beef (not cooked); salt and pepper the meat.
Sprinkle a layer of chopped onion, 3 layers of sliced potatoes, 1/2 cup grated Cheddar cheese, pork and beans and tomato soup.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350° or use crock-pot for several hours.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, nuts and garlic. Spread over ham slices. Roll like jellyroll. Chill. Slice into small pieces. Secure with toothpicks.

title: rookie cookies
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add flour and oats; mix thoroughly.
Add nuts or raisins, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: raspberry squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to margarine mixture.
Add coconut and nuts.
Batter is thick.
Grease and flour 9 x 9-inch pan (I use a 9 x 13-inch pan).
Put 2/3 batter in pan.
Spread jam over it; sprinkle rest of batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes (30 to 40 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan).

title: artichoke cheese strata
directions: Saute mushrooms and onions in margarine.
Layer half each of bread cubes, sauteed veggies, cheese, artichokes and pimientos in lightly greased 9-inch quiche dish.
Repeat layers.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Soften and combine all ingredients (do not use blender).
Form into a ball; roll in walnuts.
Chill.
Serve on a small doily with crackers or rye bread.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Top with chips.
Bake at 375° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: onion pie
directions: Melt butter in pan over low heat. Add sliced onions and cook until soft (not brown). Sprinkle flour over onions and then remove from heat.
Add eggs, bacon and milk to pan. Put in pie crust and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 45 minutes in 400° oven.
Serve hot.

title: yummy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, peanut butter, sugars, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat on medium speed of electric mixer until blended well.
Add the egg.
Beat until just blended. Mix flour, salt and baking soda in a small bowl.
Add gradually to creamy mixture on low speed.
Mix until just blended.

Roll a rounded teaspoonful into a ball with the palms of your clean hands. Press crisscross with a fork to flatten balls on cookie sheet. Bake at 375°, one cookie sheet at a time, about 7 to 9 minutes or until just browning on edges.
Cool 2 to 3 minutes on cookie sheet. Place tinfoil or brown paper bags on counter.
Scoop up cookies with flat spatula and flip over onto bags or foil.
Let cool completely before placing into sealed container.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix cream cheese and butter together.
Add sugar, then add vanilla until creamy.

title: whipped topping(diabetic)
directions: Place ice water in a small bowl; gradually add milk powder, beating at high speed of an electric mixer until soft peaks form.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar, eggs and flavorings.
Make a paste of cocoa and food coloring.
Add first mixture.
Alternate flour and buttermilk.
Add soda and salt.
Add vinegar; beat until blended well.
Bake in three layers at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: rice pudding (swedish)
directions: Cook rice and 1 cup boiling water with salt in top of boiler. Bring to boil and cook 15 minutes.
Add milk and simmer for 45 minutes.
Stir slowly into eggs; add remaining ingredients.
Pour into casserole.
Set pan in hot water and bake in hot oven (400°) for 45 minutes.
Makes six generous servings.
Eggs can be omitted and mixture served without further baking.

title: oven braised whole baby carrots
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 1-quart casserole, arrange carrots. Mix all remaining ingredients, except parsley.
Pour over carrots and toss well to coat.
(If using dried parsley, sprinkle carrots before baking.)
Cover casserole and bake until carrots are tender, 20 to 30 minutes.
(If using fresh parsley, sprinkle just before serving.)

title: lime surprise
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add ice cream at once; stir until smooth.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Pour into serving dish or mold.
Chill for at least 1/2 hour.

title: lemon bars
directions: Sift flour with 1/3 cup sugar in bowl and 2 teaspoons lemon rind.
Cut in butter and 1/4 cup cream cheese until particles are fine.
Press in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots; drain and cool.
Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add soup, salt, pepper and cheese.
Add carrots, stir until covered.
Pour into casserole dish.
Cover with stuffing mixture mixed with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Mix all together.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: yum-yum pie
directions: Soften butter; mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Put together the milk, sugar, Dream Whip and cream cheese.
Place half of cracker crumb mixture in bottom of Pyrex dish.
Spread half of Dream Whip mixture over cracker crumbs.
Then spread the berries over this mixture.
Put remainder of Dream Whip on top of berries and sprinkle remainder of crumbs on this.
Refrigerate until time to serve.

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and mushrooms; drain. Mix spaghetti and pizza sauces together. Mix cheeses together.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Fold in patience.
Do good deeds with care.
Bake in a moderate oven.
It may take a while, but the God's blessing you will have happiness with a smile.

title: perky popcorn
directions: Mix popcorn, pretzels and M&M's in a large bowl.
Combine sugar, honey and corn syrup in a 1-quart saucepan.
Bring to a full boil, stirring constantly; remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla until smooth.
Pour over popcorn mixture; toss to coat well.
Spread on baking sheet.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes, stirring after 15 minutes.
Cool.
Break into pieces. Yield:
10 cups.

title: lila's pie dough(no fail pie dough)
directions: Cut the first 4 ingredients together, then add egg, water and vinegar to fill 1 cup.
Refrigerate before you roll it.
If this fails, go to Petrucci's.

title: seabury burritos
directions: Make the guacamole according to directions on the package. Soften the tortillas by separating and placing 3 or 4 on a plate in the microwave for 10 seconds on High temperature.
Put other ingredients in bowls for easy access.
Fill each tortilla with heaping spoonful of each:
cheese, guacamole, sour cream, beans, chili and sprouts.
Roll with ends under.
Place on plate and microwave until heated through, approximately 30 seconds on High temperature.
Serve with olives and lettuce on the side.
Can place in a baking dish and warm in the oven at 350° for 20 minutes or make ahead and just heat before serving.

title: pickled beets
directions: Wash beets, leaving on root and 1-inch of tops.
Cover beets with boiling water; simmer for 25 minutes.
Drain.
Slip off skins and trim beets.
In large kettle combine vinegar, water, and sugar.
Add spices and bring to a boil.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Pack beets in hot jars leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Cover beets with hot liquid.
Put on hot lids and seal.
If lids don't seal in 15 minutes, hot bath jars.

title: cheeseburger skillet dinner
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to package directions. Meanwhile, in large skillet brown meat with onion; drain.
Stir in vegetables, catsup, water, mustard and garlic powder.
Cook until vegetables are crisp-tender, about 10 minutes.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Mix in macaroni and cheese.
Season to taste. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: lynn's potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes. Press out liquid. Mix all ingredients. Bake in large casserole dish for 1 hour at 350° (325° if glass).

title: brownie pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheet to 350°.
In medium saucepan, melt chocolate and margarine.
Cool slightly.
Mix together water, egg yolks, vanilla and brown sugar.
Stir into chocolate.
Fold in flour and salt.
Beat egg whites until stiff, then fold into chocolate.
Add pecans.
Spread into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: all good pie(50 years old)
directions: Mix sugar, butter, eggs, water and flour.
Stir in vanilla and pecans.
Add vinegar last.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 400° for approximately 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 325° for 45 minutes.
Makes 1 large or 2 small pies.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Next, add eggs and mix, then add the pumpkin and water and mix.
Next, add gradually the flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and cloves and mix thoroughly.
Finally, add nuts and/or raisins if desired.
Bake in greased and floured pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: curly dock
directions: Boil leaves for 10 minutes and add seasonings.
Young leaves may be used raw in fresh salads.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar, zucchini, oil, raisins, nuts and vanilla. Mix cinnamon, cocoa, flour, salt, soda and baking powder together.
Add gradually to wet ingredients. Pour into 2 well-greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until done. I use 3 pans instead of 2.

title: banana walnut buttermilk bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar and butter; add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.

Beat mashed bananas and vanilla and continue beating until smooth. In a measuring cup, stir baking soda into the buttermilk and add to banana mixture along with flour and chopped nuts. Stir the batter until it is just combined. Pour batter into greased and floured 9 x 5 loaf pan. Bake 1 hour. Transfer bread to rack and let cool for 10 minutes. Then turn bread out of pan and let cool completely on rack.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 150° for 5 minutes.
In a small bowl, combine yeast, water and sugar.
In a microwave bowl, heat margarine 2 1/2 minutes; add cold water, sugar, salt and eggs.
Add water and yeast to the mixture.
Pour flour into mixture.
Stir well.
Turn onto floured board; knead 5 minutes.
Add more flour if too sticky.
Put into greased Dutch oven and let rise until doubled, about 1 hour, in oven.
Heat oven to 150°; divide dough in 1/4's. Roll out into circles.
Cut in 8 pieces, like pizza.
Roll into crescents. Let rise 45 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water, add other ingredients; mix. Refrigerate until set.

title: gregory's spanish vegetable
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cook broccoli as directed on package except just until heated through; drain.
Mix broccoli and Velveeta process cheese spread.
Spoon into greased 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with crumbs; dot with margarine.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: caramel custard pie
directions: Mix sugar, melted butter and egg yolks together.
Mix 1/2 cup of the milk with flour and shake; add to mixture.
Heat 1 1/2 cups milk to lukewarm and add to mixture.
Beat egg whites (not stiff) and vanilla; add to mixture and put in pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes; after that, turn temperature down to 375° for 35 minutes.

title: black bing cherry jello salad
directions: Drain cherries and add enough water to juice to make 2 cups. Heat and dissolve jello in juice.
Add Coke and let cool.
When the jello begins to congeal, add pecans and cherries.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: olallaberry cheesecake with berry wine sauce
directions: Stir together above ingredients and press crumb mixture evenly onto the bottom of a greased 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: "the best" oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine eggs, raisins and vanilla and let stand for 1 hour, covered with plastic.
Cream together butter and sugars.
Add flour, salt, cinnamon and soda to sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Blend in egg and raisin mixture, oatmeal and nuts.
Dough will be stiff. Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or light brown.
Delicious.
Secret is soaking the raisins.

title: christmas cherry tarts
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Grease two 1 3/4-inch tartlet or small cupcake pans. Combine graham cracker crumbs with butter or margarine; press a rounded teaspoonful of crumb mixture into each cupcake pan. Beat cream cheese, vanilla, egg and sugar until well blended. Fill each cupcake pan. Bake 10 minutes. Chill thoroughly. When ready to serve, run a thin knife around each tart and lift out of pan. Top with a pie cherry. Makes 24.

title: chunky peanut butter pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and powdered sugar well.
Add Cool Whip and peanut butter; blend well.
Pour into cooled graham cracker crust.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Brown hamburger meat, onion and green pepper.
Mix beans and barbecue sauce together and add hamburger mixture.
Simmer for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Bake crescent rolls in 10 x 15-inch pan.
(Spread out to form crust.)
Cool.
Mix softened cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing.
Spread on crust.
Cover with veggies of your choice: tomatoes, peppers, cauliflower, broccoli, carrots, olives, mushrooms, radishes, etc.
Cover with wax paper.
Press down with cutting board.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat all ingredients until foamy.
Pour into an unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°, then 350° until firm.

title: basic spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan.
Add meat or vegetables, depending on preference.
Simmer at least 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Pour over noodles.

title: brownie cookies
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake at 350° on well-greased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool 1 minute, then remove from sheet.
Frost, if desired.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: chocolate dipped medjools
directions: Pit dates and stuff with walnut.
Melt candiquick in microwave.
Be very careful not to get any drops of water in it. Microwave for about 3 minutes.
Dip dates in melted candiquick and place on a sheet of clear plastic wrap.
Candy sticks too hard to other surfaces.
Let cool 1/2 hour.

title: vegetable stew
directions: Saute onions in 3 tablespoons oil until clear.
Add carrots; continue stirring.
Add oleo; stir.
When melted, add flour and stir.
Add water and stir.
Let cook until carrots seem soft.
Add peas, ham and spices.
Cook until hot.
(Other leftover meats such as roast beef can be used instead of ham.)
Low in fat and sodium.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: In a skillet, cook bacon until crisp; drain thoroughly. Crumble bacon.
Remove stems from mushrooms and wash mushrooms. Drain off water.
Dry mushroom caps.
Combine rest of ingredients and fill mushroom caps.
Arrange in single layer in a sided pan and cook, covered with foil, for 20 to 25 minutes at 325°.
Serve hot.

title: gulab jamun
directions: First make the syrup.
In a 4-quart pot, combine 4 cups water, the sugar and the cardamom; simmer until sugar is dissolved.
Do not stir.
Pour half the syrup into a serving bowl.
Leave the other half in the pot with the cardamom pods.
Combine the powdered milk, flour, oil and milk in a bowl.
Make a soft dough. Make small smooth balls out of the dough, about 1-inch in diameter.
(Should make about 2 dozen Jamuns.)

title: 4 layer chocolate pie
directions: First Layer:
Mix first four ingredients.
Blend and press in bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: taco pie
directions: Grease a 13-inch baking dish.
Mix corn muffin mix.
Add salsa; pour 1/2 in dish.
Brown beef; drain.
Add taco mix and tomato sauce; pour on top of corn muffin mix.
Pour other 1/2 on top.
Grate cheese; sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: honey mustard dressing
directions: Put honey, vinegar, mustard, lemon juice, onion, poppy seed, salt and 1/4 cup oil in blender.
Process at medium-high. Immediately remove feeder cap and pour in remaining oil in a steady stream.
Cover; continue to process until well blended. Makes about 1 3/4 cups.

title: apple pecan squares
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs, soda, flour, apples, vanilla extract and pecans.
Mix well. Spread evenly in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour.
Pour Caramel Glaze over warm cake. Cool.
Cut into squares for serving.

title: doris miller's egg salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add salt, pepper and lemon juice to taste.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt margarine.
Cool a little and add all ingredients and mix well.
Bake in rectangular pan for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Cook rice. Saute onions in butter.
Mix soup, Cheez Whiz, broccoli, rice and onions.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 15 minutes.

title: beef-broccoli wellington
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In medium skillet, brown meat; drain well. Add broccoli, cheese, onion, sour cream, salt and pepper; mix well.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Separate dough into 4 long rectangles.
On ungreased cookie sheet, overlap long sides of 2 rectangles 1/2-inch; firmly press edges and perforations to seal. Press or roll to form a 13 x 7-inch rectangle.
Spoon meat mixture in a 3-inch strip, lengthwise down center of dough.
Bring long edges of dough rectangle over filling, overlapping edges slightly. Pinch edge and ends to seal.
Repeat with remaining rectangles. Brush with beaten egg; sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 22 minutes, or until deep golden brown.
Garnish as desired. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In large bowl, mix together soup, milk, chicken, peas, carrots and pepper.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Unfold one pie crust; place in a 9-inch pie plate.
Press firmly against plate.
Pour filling mixture into pie crust.
Cover with remaining pie crust; seal edges.
Brush beaten egg over top of pie crust.
Using a sharp knife, cut 1-inch slits in top of crust (steam vent).
Place pie on a rimmed baking sheet.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until crust is golden.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Mix together the first 8 ingredients.
Cut green peppers in 1-inch rings; stuff them and bake in shallow pan 30 minutes at 350°.
Put ketchup and cheese mixture on top and bake 10 minutes more.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beat well. Add flour and Seven-Up.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: copper carrots
directions: Cook carrots in water until tender.
In another pan, cover onion and peppers with water and just bring to a boil.
Mix tomato soup, sugar, oil, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper. Drain water from carrots, onion and peppers in a bowl and add to soup mixture.
Cover.
Let stand several hours before serving. Will keep for days in refrigerator.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Fold in cranberry sauce and pineapple (undrained).
Chill until thickened.
Stir in wine and nuts.
Pour in large mold and chill until set.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Rinse the beef slices and then line a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with them. Wrap each chicken breast with a slice of bacon and place in pan. Mix sour cream and soup. Pour over chicken. Bake, uncovered, at 250° for 3 hours.

title: rice cooker jambalaya
directions: Brown sausage and pour off grease. Place all ingredients in electric rice cooker; stir to blend. Cover and press button to cook. When the bell rings, it's ready. Serve 4 to 6.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Drain mixed fruit; slice bananas.
Mix with cottage cheese, sour cream and coconut.
Refrigerate for one hour before serving. Serves 4.

title: aunt ruth's pinwheel cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, brown sugar, shortening, peanut butter and egg.
Sift together flour, salt and baking soda and add to creamed mixture.
Pat down on greased wax paper.
Melt chocolate chips and pour over dough.
Roll up and chill 1/2 hour or more. Slice and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: apple torte
directions: Pare and chop apples.
Sift dry ingredients together and combine all.
Spread in buttered Pyrex plate.
Bake in a 350° oven until apples are soft, about 30 minutes.
Serve hot or cold with whipped cream or your favorite pudding sauce.

title: pineapple salad
directions: In medium saucepan on medium heat, melt marshmallows in milk. Add mayonnaise, 1 box lime Jell-O and cream cheese.
Mix until Jell-O and cheese is blended. Add drained pineapple. In large mixing bowl, whip Carnation cream until stiff; fold pineapple mixture into stiff Carnation milk.
Chill in refrigerator until set. Mix remaining lime Jell-O as directed using pineapple liquid and cold water. Pour over pineapple mixture; put in refrigerator until set.

title: graham cracker crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place graham crackers on sheet.
Melt butter and sugar in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Pour over graham crackers.
Sprinkle pecans over and place in oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Watch; don't let burn.
Take out and let cool.

title: herbed tomato bread(3 layers)
directions: Make a dough and knead it 12 times.
Spread on bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: rice casserole
directions: Brown onion in stick of oleo margarine.
Add rice and brown a few minutes.
Then add beef consomme and a handful of grated cheese.
Put in deep casserole, cover and cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: *holly leaf clusters
directions: Put marshmallows and margarine in heavy saucepan and melt. Add vanilla and food coloring; blend well.
Add corn flakes and slowly stir until all are coated with the green mixture.
Put on wax paper in small clumps.
While still warm, decorate each with 2 or 3 bright red cinnamon candies.
Makes 24 to 30.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Peel carrots, slice and cook in a small amount of water until tender.
Drain and cool.
Place a layer of carrots in a shallow dish.
Top with a layer of green pepper and then onion.
Repeat layering.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cream butter with sugar.
Add beaten egg, stirring slowly.
In separate bowl, combine dry ingredients (flour, baking powder and salt).
Slowly add flour mixture to egg mixture, a little at a time, alternating with the milk, and stirring only enough to mix.
(Batter will be lumpy.)
Stir 2 tablespoons flour into blueberries, then fold berries into batter. Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.
Makes 12.

title: hot potato casserole
directions: Cut potatoes into bite-size pieces and boil until done.
Be sure to drain potatoes.
Put in casserole dish.
Put 1/2 of the melted margarine and all other ingredients together and mix with potatoes, except corn flake crumbs.
Mix corn flake crumbs with the other 1/2 stick of margarine and pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: minted peas
directions: Shell and rinse peas.
Cook peas in boiling water to cover 10 to 12 minutes or until tender.
Drain, reserving 1/4 cup liquid. Return peas and reserved liquid to pan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, 2 to 3 minutes or until mint sauce melts.

title: danish apple cake
directions: Grease an ovenproof dish and line with a layer of breadcrumbs. Dot with lumps of butter.
Sprinkle with sugar to taste and cover with a thick layer of peeled and sliced apples.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Combine in large container.
Makes 100 cups.
Add 1/3 cup cocoa mix to 1 cup water for each 1 cup serving.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut cauliflower, green onions and radishes.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and onion dip.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: granny's poor folk's pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Mix flour and cocoa with sugar and butter mixture.
Add eggs and milk.
Mix well and put in 2 pie shells.
Bake at 375° for approximately 30 minutes until crusty on top.

title: mexican cornbread and turkey or chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cornbread mix and pour into 10-inch casserole dish.
Prepare cornbread mix according to directions. Pour over mixture.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.

title: fruit conserve
directions: Place all in a large kettle.
Add
water and cook until fruit thaws.
Add 1/2 cup sugar.	Continue cooking until dates can be pricked easily.

title: pea casserole
directions: Mix soup, sour cream and salt.
Stir in peas.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Top with cracker crumbs and cheese; pour butter over all.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes or until bubbling.
Top with onion rings and brown.
Serve hot.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon half and half cream and sugar until smooth.
Stir in thawed Cool Whip and spread in bottom of graham cracker crust.
Place in refrigerator and allow to cool.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt oleo, oil and marshmallows together.
Pour over mixture of popped corn, peanuts, gumdrops and M&M's.
Press into tube pan. Cover for 30 to 40 minutes before removing from pan.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Prepare stuffing according to package.
Use the broth from cooked chicken in the stuffing.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place 1 package of stuffing on bottom.
Next, layer cut up cooked chicken. Drain green beans.
Layer beans next, then other package of stuffing.
Mix cream of chicken soup with 3/4 can of chicken broth.
Pour over top.
Bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: french cocoa pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Pour into pie shell and bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients and put into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Melt the margarine and add the crackers to it. Stir until the crumbs are damp and have absorbed all the margarine. Sprinkle on vegetable mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: jello fruit mold
directions: Mix the pineapple and jello in pan; bring to a boil.
Cool. Add the remaining ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Put in either a large bowl or a mold ring.
Let jell.

title: yeast rolls
directions: First scald milk.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Mix sugar, salt and shortening.
Add warm milk and mix. Add beaten egg. Add yeast and flour. Mix well.
Cover.
Let rise for 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down to put on floured board.
Pinch off into rolls. Place in a greased baking dish.
Let rise again about 1 1/2 hours. Bake in a 250° oven for 1/2 hour.
Turn up to 300° and bake until brown. Brush top with butter.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Saute 1 teaspoon olive oil, basil and onion until brown.
Add crushed tomatoes, tomato paste and water.
Simmer for 1 hour. Serve over any pasta.
Can put meatballs in sauce.

title: cheese and beef casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except for cheese. Place 1/2 of mixture in casserole dish; cover with 1/4 pound of cheese.
Put remaining meat mixture on top of cheese.
Place in oven and cook for 1 hour.

title: angel strawberry delight
directions: Dissolve jello, add strawberries and ice cream.
Stir until dissolved.
Put in refrigerator until thickened.
Fold in cake pieces.
Pour in 3-quart casserole dish.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve. Garnish with whipped topping and fresh strawberries.
This can be made with other fruits, such as peaches and peach jello.

title: broccoli-cheese squares
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with butter. Steam broccoli until partially cooked, about 3 minutes.
Cool and press dry. Beat eggs and milk until frothy.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook onions in oil in large pan until tender.
Add tomatoes, water, sherry, seasoning mix, corn, beans, Worcestershire and salt. Simmer covered 15 minutes.
Add chicken, okra and zucchini.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream shortening with sugars.
Add well beaten egg, crushed pineapple and flavoring.
Beat thoroughly.
Sift flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Add nuts to flour, mix thoroughly and add dry ingredients to pineapple and egg mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 1 1/2-quart dish. Mix flour, sugar and milk. Pour into melted margarine.
Do not stir.
Add fruit.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with ice cream, if desired, and serve hot.

title: apple cup cakes
directions: Cream sugar and oil well; add egg.
Beat until frothy.
Add grated apples with soda mixed in.
Add dry ingredients a little at a time, beating between each addition.
Add nuts and dates or raisins and mix well.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 12 cupcakes.
These freeze well.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Bring strawberries and lemon juice concentrate to a boil, mashing constantly.
Boil for three minutes, while mashing.
Add sugar and boil for 7 to 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour into glass cake pan and stir often until cool.
Leave to set overnight.
Store in jars and refrigerate.

title: tuna salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix flour, 3/4 cup sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add milk and stir until smooth.
Pour batter over melted butter and peaches over batter.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ham steak
directions: Combine mustard, honey and orange or lemon peel.
Brush over ham steak.
Grill for 4 minutes per side.

title: meat casserole
directions: Saute hamburger and drain grease.
Mix with rest of ingredients.
Bake in uncovered casserole at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, until solid.

title: veal scallopini with marsala
directions: Flatten the meat slices slightly with your hands.
In a bowl, combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge scallopini on both sides with flour mixture.
In a skillet, heat butter until lightly brown.
Add scallopini.
Saute about 2 minutes.
Turn slices over. Saute on other side for 1 to 2 minutes or until meat is done to your liking.
Add Marsala to skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Cook for 1 to 2 minutes.
Serve scallopini immediately with wine juices.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Bake 30 minutes at 400° for 5 minutes, then at 350° for 15 minutes.
The last 10 minutes, sprinkle canned French fried onions over top; return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: layered salad
directions: Tear lettuce into small pieces and put in bottom of glass bowl.
Layer with remaining vegetables, ending with cheese and bacon bits.
Mix sour cream, mayo and dressing mix; spread on top. Top with bacon bits. This dish is great for cookouts and homecomings.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Fold in 6 beaten egg whites and 1/2 cup of sugar that have been combined in a mixer until stiff.
Pour into 3 large, unbaked pie shells.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°, then at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: crabmeat appetizers
directions: Split English muffins and place on cookie sheet.
Mix all ingredients together and spread on muffin halves.
Bake at 400° in broiler for 10 minutes.
Cut each muffin into 4 pieces and serve.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add chicken, taco mix, 3/4 cup water and salsa.
Simmer.
Cook broccoli or spinach; drain.
Chop finely (I use food processor).
Add to hamburger mix and wrap in tortilla shells (like burritos).
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread sour cream over top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all together and bake for 12 to 15 minutes or until done.

title: fruit delight
directions: In a bowl, combine the Cool Whip topping and the package of jello, stirring occasionally, until completely mixed.
In another bowl, mix the fruit and Planters peanuts.
In a large dessert bowl, layer the Cool Whip mixture, alternating with the fruit mixture, until the bowl is full.
Refrigerate for an hour before serving.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: sunshine dill pickles
directions: Wash pickles and quarter.
Pack
firmly
in jars with 2 clove garlic and 2 sprigs
dill
in
each
jar.
Heat
rest of ingredients;
pour over pickles
and put lid and ring on.
Set in sun for 3 weeks.
A double batch makes 6 1/2 quarts.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together.
Chill at least one hour before serving.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding as package instructions call for, then fold in Cool Whip and set this all aside.
In large baking pan (with lid), put frosting on graham cracker and line bottom, making 1st layer. Next, add 1/2-inch layer of the pudding mixture.
Repeat your layers as listed; make sure your top layers are the frosted graham crackers.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix and divide into 2 pie crusts.
Let stand overnight.
Put cherries on top.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and press all water out of spinach.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate 2 hours before serving. Great with vegetables or chips.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Drain juice off package of frozen strawberries.
Melt marshmallows in juice, using a double boiler.
Add strawberries to 2 cups whipped cream.
Add to marshmallow/juice mixture.
Pour over cooled crust.
Refrigerate.

title: coffeecake
directions: Mix well and add 1/2 cups nuts or raisins and sprinkle over cake.
Place the cake in your Dutch oven on the stones and bake in coals about 15 minutes.
Turn occasionally so all sides are evenly heated.

title: banana freeze
directions: Mash bananas and add all ingredients in large bowl. Freeze in flat bowl overnight, or until set.

title: butter barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onions and saute until tender. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Use on your favorite meat.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat until fluffy.
Add flour and salt; fold in lemon extract and 7-Up.
Pour into tube pan and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Do not open oven door until done.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown meat.
Add onions and garlic last minute.
Season. Dissolve bouillon cube in hot water and add meat.
Cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Add tomatoes and green pepper.
Cook 10 minutes longer.
Combine remaining ingredients and stir into meat. Bring to boil.
Cook, stirring constantly, 5 minutes longer. Serve with hot Chinese noodles or rice.

title: berry best
directions: Put berries, sugar, butter cut into pieces and hot water in bottom of a 3 quart
baking
dish.
In
a
medium
bowl
mix flour, sugar, margarine and
milk well.
Place dough mixture in top of baking dish over the
berries.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift first 6 ingredients together; add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool and remove from pans.

title: strawberry dessert(pretzel salad)
directions: Mix together and press into a 9 x 13 Pyrex pan. Bake at 400° for 8 minutes. Cool.

title: pilaf
directions: Melt butter or margarine in pan (low-medium heat).
Add vermicelli or angel hair macaroni.
Stir/cook until golden brown. Add rice; stir it a little until mixed.
Add at least 2 cans chicken broth now and the other one later when rice cooks down. Add broth and stir.
Cook over medium heat.
Put on lid.
Cook for about 20 minutes.
I stir mine every so often.

title: low-fat pasta and red peppers
directions: Cook pasta as directed on package, omitting salt and oil. Drain.
Coat a nonstick skillet with cooking spray; add margarine. Heat on medium-high until margarine melts.
Add pepper, onions and garlic.
Saute until tender.
Stir in Italian dressing; cook until heated.
Add pasta, tossing gently, just until mixture is thoroughly heated.
Season with black pepper and grated Parmesan cheese.
I sometimes add sliced grilled chicken breasts and cooked turkey Italian sausage.
Great meal!

title: cabbage with apples and cider
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling water for 5 minutes; drain and squeeze dry.
Put in casserole dish with cider, water, cloves, nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Place cut apples on top.
Top with butter.
Heat in 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: mini fruit cakes
directions: Mix dates, nuts and flour together.
Melt margarine and butter; let cool.
Add to dry mixture.
Add sugar, egg yolks and vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Line small muffin tins with paper and fill half full.
Bake at 325° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Makes 8 1/2 dozen.

title: fried corn
directions: Shuck and silk corn.
Scrape corn off cob; mix with milk, cornstarch and seasoning.
Melt butter in skillet.
Pour all ingredients into skillet; cook on medium-low until tender, adding milk as needed.
Makes 6 healthy servings.

title: potatoes and hamburger dinner
directions: Cut foil large enough for 4 dinners.
Wrap 2 hamburger patties, topped with potato-onion mixture, tightly in foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
You can also add sliced carrots, if desired, and bake as directed.

title: barbecued franks
directions: Cut each frank into thirds.
In a large bowl, stir together all ingredients.
Place in two 13 x 9-inch pans with franks in a single layer.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes or until franks are hot and glazed.
Serve warm with toothpicks.

title: turner's texas dip
directions: Put in double boiler all ingredients; heat until cheese is melted, stirring occasionally.
Serve with corn chips.

title: party ryes
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Spread on slices of cocktail bread to edges.
Arrange on cookie sheet and place under broiler for 3 to 4 minutes until brown.
Makes approximately 20 appetizers.

title: whiskey mix
directions: Mix coffee and ice cream with 1 cup light rum and four cups blended whiskey.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add chocolate.
Stir over low heat until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boiling point. Makes 1 1/2 cups sauce.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Add flour and pecans. Blend well, then spread evenly in pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown. Let cool.

title: angel flake cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake about 15 minutes at 350°.

title: sunsetview restaurant sunshine chili
directions: In a heavy-duty pot, brown beef in fat.
Add onion, bell pepper, water, catsup, seasonings and bouillon cubes.
Slowly simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add cooked noodles. Mix well and simmer 5 or more minutes.
Serve topped with cheese and raw onions.
Serve with crackers or garlic bread.

title: corn dish
directions: Combine and mix well.
Spread 1/2 mixture in greased baking dish.
Cover with 1 small can green chiles, drained and 6 ounces Monterey Jack cheese (slices are best).
Spread remainder of mixture.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: eggnog
directions: In a small mixer bowl, beat egg yolks until blended. Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar, beating at high speed until thick and lemon colored.
Stir in milk, vanilla and salt.
Chill thoroughly the whipped cream. Wash beaters well.

title: clam chowder
directions: Combine potatoes, onion, celery, parsley, water and salt in saucepan.
Cook on low until vegetables are tender.
Mash some of the potatoes with a fork.
Drain clams, reserving juice.
Add clams and milk to vegetable mixture; heat just to boiling. Combine clam juice and flour, making a smooth paste.
Stir into chowder; heat until slightly thickened.
Stir constantly.

title: chicken & cornbread dressing
directions: Boil chicken until tender (about 45 minutes).
Remove chicken from stock.
Soak cornbread and toast or biscuits in 4 cups of stock and milk or water.
Saute onion and celery in margarine until golden.
Combine bread and onion mix with eggs, salt, pepper and seasoning.
Add cream of chicken or mushroom soup and 4 cups of stock to moisten.
Chop chicken and add to mixture.
Cook at 325 for 1 hour.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Mix cake by directions.
While cooking, mix Cool Whip and candy bars.
When cake cools, poke holes in top.
Pour ice cream topping over cake and ice with Cool Whip mixture.
Keep refrigerated.

title: any kind fruit cobbler
directions: Put fruit in baking dish (if fresh fruit, cover with 1 cup sugar).
Cut butter up over fruit.
Mix milk, sugar, flour and vanilla and pour over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until brown on top.

title: punch bowl delight
directions: In punch bowl or attractive deep dish, crumble 1/2 of the cake. Mix gel with strawberries. Pour over cake. Add remaining cake, then pudding, pineapple, coconut and pecans. Spread Cool Whip over top and add reserved strawberries. Serve with large spoon.

title: onion and sour cream dip
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except vegetables.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serve with vegetable dippers.
Makes 1 1/2 cups dip.

title: granola(breakfast cereal)
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 300° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Turn every 10 minutes.
Keep in airtight container, in refrigerator.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Blend the first 3 ingredients together; spread on bottom of a large pan or casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until light brown; cool.
Mix the next 4 ingredients together; spread over cool crust.
Prepare chocolate pudding according to package directions; pour over mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for several hours.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring butter, water and cocoa to a boil.
Add the flour, sugar and salt.
Beat the eggs, sour cream and soda in separate bowl; add to flour mixture.
Beat well.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375° in a large cookie sheet.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: no-fat cream cheese frosting
directions: Blend all ingredients together with electric mixer until smooth and creamy.
Chill in refrigerator 1/2 to 1 hour before spreading.

title: nutty marshmallow bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir chopped peanuts, flour, oats, brown sugar, baking soda, salt and egg in a large bowl.
Stir in margarine with a fork until mixture is crumbly.
Press in an ungreased rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Bake 10 minutes. Spoon Marshmallow Creme over hot layer.
Let stand 1 minute; spread evenly.
Drizzle topping over Creme.
Sprinkle with 1 1/2 cups of peanuts.
Bake until golden brown (20 minutes).
Let stand until cool, then loosen edges from side of pan.
Cut into bars.

title: chili con carne(microwave cooking)
directions: Crumble ground beef into baking dish.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 4 minutes.
Drain meat and break up with fork.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook, covered, on 70% Power (Roast) for 15 to 18 minutes or until hot.
Stir once during cooking time.
Adjust seasonings.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 4.

title: semi-sweet nut cake
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, chocolate bits and nuts.
Add milk last.
Bake in tube pan at 350° about 1 hour.

title: baked chop suey
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Combine with other ingredients and bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: potato candy
directions: Wash, then boil potato in jacket.
When done, peel and mash in bowl with a stiff fork.
Add the sifted powdered sugar a little at a time.
Add vanilla.
Continue adding sugar until you have a very stiff dough. Roll out on wax paper that's sprinkled with powdered sugar.
May have to sprinkle dough so you can roll it out.
Then spread peanut butter on and roll jelly roll style.
Slice and ready to eat.
This is rich.
You may use sweet potato instead of Irish.

title: cheese sauce substitute
directions: Blend until smooth.
Very good as a replacement for cheese in macaroni.

title: beginner biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix marmalade and butter; spread in square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches.
Stir baking mix and water to a soft dough. Gently smooth dough into a ball on floured cloth-covered board. Knead 5 times.
Roll dough into an 8-inch square; place on marmalade mixture in pan.
Pat dough evenly into corners; cut into 36 squares.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Invert onto heatproof plate. Serve warm.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into an uncooked 9-inch pie shell of your choice and top with a solid or lattice crust, being sure sufficient breathing holes exist.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 40 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: pistachio pineapple pie
directions: Combine butter	and
coconut.
Press into a 9-inch pan. Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Cool crust.

title: lasagna
directions: Crumble hamburger; cook and drain off grease. Add diced tomatoes, tomato paste, onions and spices. Simmer for 1/2 hour. Cook 8 lasagna noodles. In a glass 9 x 12 baking dish, make layers of meat sauce, mushrooms, noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese. Repeat for second layer. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes. Let set for 1/2 hour after baking.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll pastry to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into 12 (1-inch) squares.
Pare and quarter apples.
Place 2 quarters, sprinkling with sugar and cinnamon, in pie crust square and fold up corners, pinching crust together at top.

title: pickle wheels
directions: Drain pickles and dry with paper towel.
Soften cheese so it will spread easy.
Spread cheese on one side of bread.
Place pickle on one side and roll up.
Pinch bread gently to hold together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Slice and serve.

title: squash dressing
directions: Saute onion, pepper, and celery in margarine until tender. Add to cornbread and stir well. Stir in remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour into 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish. Bake at 400° for 50 minutes or until lightly browned. Makes 8 servings.

title: bundt coffee cake(low-fat cake)
directions: Mix ingredients and beat for 8 minutes at medium speed.
Pour 1/2 of the batter into a Bundt pan sprayed with Pam.
Cover with sugar, cinnamon and chopped nuts.
Cover with last half of batter; sprinkle cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well and pour into graham cracker crust pie shells.
Put in freezer to firm up.

title: reuben sandwiches
directions: Spread each slice of bread with the dressing.
Layer slices of corned beef on 4 slices.
Top with sauerkraut.
Add slices of Swiss cheese to the stack.
Close sandwich with remaining bread.
Butter outsides of slices and grill sandwiches in a large skillet or griddle over medium-low flame until browned on both sides and cheese has melted.
Yield:
4 sandwiches.

title: mix in pan brownies
directions: Melt shortening in baking pan.
Stir in sugar.
Add beaten eggs to mixture.
Continue stirring and add remaining ingredients. Place pan in a 375° oven and bake for 40 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put sugar, syrup, water and salt on hot fire.
Stir until it starts to boil.
Wash down sides of kettle with wet cloth.
Cover until it steams well.
Remove cover, insert candy thermometer and cook to 275°.
Add peanuts and butter.
Stir constantly, until peanuts are roasted.
Remove from fire.
Mix soda and vanilla; stir into candy.
Pour onto a buttered marble slab.
Spread thin. Allow to harden.
Break.

title: spicy shrimp with fusilli
directions: In a large skillet, lightly saute shrimp in butter.
Add pasta sauce, Tabasco sauce, salt and pepper. Simmer, covered, until shrimp are cooked. Spoon sauce over hot cooked pasta; toss to coat well.
Top pasta with shrimp.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: uznia garner's persimmon pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan that has been greased and sprinkled with dry granulated sugar. This makes crunchy edges.
Cook for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate chiffon cake(makes about 12 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt chocolate in hot water; set aside. Beat egg whites in large bowl until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar and beat until stiff and glossy; set aside.

Combine melted chocolate mixture, egg yolks, flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla in small bowl; beat 1 minute with electric mixer. Carefully fold chocolate mixture into egg whites until blended. Pour into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until top springs back when lightly touched.
Invert in pan; cool completely.
Remove from pan; sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: tortillas roll-ups
directions: In a large skillet, cook onion in oil until tender and crisp. Drain tomatoes and reserve liquid.
Add liquid and oregano to skillet and cook over high heat for 3 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in meat and chilies; remove from heat.
Spoon chicken mixture on each tortilla and roll up.
Add remaining oil to skillet and lightly brown roll-ups.
Chop tomatoes and stir in vinegar.
Pour this over roll-ups.
Cover and cook over low heat for 3 minutes.

title: frozen waldorf salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Combine the syrup, eggs, sugar, lemon juice and salt in double boiler and cook until thick.
(Mix well with wire whisk before heating to keep eggs from cooking before mixed in - doing this, mixture may be heated directly on stove.)
Cool.
Add pineapple, apples, celery, nuts, marshmallows and cool ship. Freeze.
Serve on lettuce.
Tastes best when set out a few minutes before serving.

title: spread for french bread
directions: Blend mayonnaise, margarine and other ingredients.
Spread on French bread halves and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Slice and serve.

title: brown sugar pecan cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix margarine, brown sugar and egg. Stir remaining
ingredients.
Drop
by
teaspoon
(about
1/2 teaspoon for
each) 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Dough
will flatten and spread.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until set.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and shape into small walnut sized balls.
Place on waxed paper and set aside.
In a double boiler, melt chocolates and paraffin.
Dip each ball into mixture, returning to cookie sheet lined with waxed paper.
Chill to serve. Can be left out for some time, but must be refrigerated for storage.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender (can use 4 cans carrots, 14.5 ounces each). Set aside. In pan, heat until boiling, then cool slightly the vegetable oil, vinegar, sugar, tomato soup, prepared mustard and Worcestershire sauce. Pour over the carrots, onion and green pepper. Let cool completely. Place in the refrigerator and let marinate overnight. Serve cold or warm if desired.

title: sangria
directions: Add sliced oranges and bananas; pour over ice and serve.

title: busy woman's pie
directions: Lightly grease a 10 x 5-inch Pyrex pan.
Put into pan the cherry pie filling and pineapple.
Do not mix.
Top with dry cake mix (on top of cherry pie filling and pineapple).
Pour melted butter over the entire mixture.
Place chopped nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake mix browns.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix salad oil, Worcestershire sauce, catsup, sugar and vinegar well and add remaining ingredients.

title: french roasted peanuts
directions: Place all ingredients in saucepan, except vanilla.
Cook until crystallized.
(The crystallization will form suddenly.)
Remove immediately from heat and add vanilla.
Pour into buttered cookie sheet and sprinkle lightly with salt.
Bake at 300° for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix sour cream, soup, chilies, cheese and onion.
Divide sauce in half.
Add chicken to one half.
Soften tortillas in hot oil. Put chicken mixture on hot tortillas.
Roll up and place in casserole, one layer.
Cover with remaining sauce and more shredded cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and jello.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: mexican chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil the chicken breast halves in approximately 2 quarts of water with 2 sticks of celery until tender.
Remove chicken and celery from the water.
Let chicken cool; remove from bone.
Throw celery away.
Bring chicken water to a boil.
Add the chicken broth, chicken soup and margarine.
Cut tortillas into strips, then cut strips into thirds or fourths.
Drop into the chicken broth; stir very gently.
Stir in milk.
Stir.
Add chicken; let cook over low heat for awhile.

title: baked beans
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: laverne's green chile and chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Chop when cooled.
Brown onion and garlic in butter.
Combine in a bowl, onion, garlic, soups, broth, chiles and chicken.
Put into a greased baking dish (9 x 12-inch) in alternate layers of chicken mixture, tortillas and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Soak bread in milk 5 minutes. Add sugar, butter and salt. Pour slowly over eggs. Add vanilla and mix well.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: crab casserole
directions: Mix oleo, flour and milk.
Add remaining ingredients.
Grease casserole; put in mixture and cover with buttered bread crumbs. Bake 3/4 hour at 300°.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream together brown sugar and shortening.
Beat in egg and applesauce.
In another bowl combine remaining ingredients.
Stir flour mixture into applesauce mixture until well blended.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until almost no indentation remains when touched.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet; cool.
Frost, if desired.
Yield:
3 dozen cookies.

title: cheese omelet with herbed mushroom sauce
directions: Bring spaghetti sauce and mushrooms to boil and simmer.
Whip eggs with cream or milk.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Beat slightly.
Heat butter or margarine in skillet; add eggs and cook slowly.
When somewhat firm, place cheese on top.
Run spatula around edge; fold omelet in half over cheese.
When golden brown, lift onto plate and served with herbed mushroom sauce.

title: frothy apple cooler
directions: In blender, combine all ingredients.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings, only 59 calories each.

title: chicken-almond stir-fry
directions: Pour oil around top of a preheated wok, coating sides, or in a large, nonstick skillet. Heat briefly at medium-high (375°). Add chicken and almonds; cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Add frozen vegetables; cover and cook 4 minutes, stirring once. Combine cornstarch and next 4 ingredients; add to wok. Cook, stirring constantly, 2 to 3 minutes or until mixture thickens. Serve over rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: toffee
directions: Butter pan.
Spread almonds in pan.
Heat sugar and butter to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil seven minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Immediately spread mixture over nuts in pan.
Sprinkle chocolate pieces over hot mixture.

title: smothered steak
directions: Cut steak into strips.
Put steak strips, flour, salt and pepper in crock-pot; stir well and coat steak.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Cover; cook in crock-pot on high for 1 hour, then turn on low and cook for 8 hours.
Or, cook on high for 5 hours. Serve over rice.
Delicious!

title: peaches-n-cream
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together flour, pudding mix and baking powder.
Combine egg, milk and melted butter; add to dry ingredients.
Mix well; spread in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Drain peaches, reserve 1/3 cup liquid, sprinkle atop batter. Beat together cream cheese, the 1/2 cup sugar and reserved peach liquid, pour atop peaches in pan.
Combine the 1 tablespoon sugar and the cinnamon, sprinkle over all. bake in 350° oven 45 minutes. Cool.
Serves 9.

title: crab corn chowder
directions: Simmer about 10 minutes.

title: norwegian lemon bonbons
directions: Blend butter and sugar until light.
Add cornstarch and flour, sifted together.
Mix well.
Chill until dough can be handled easily.
Shape into small balls (walnut sized).
Spread nuts on waxed paper and sweeten with a little sugar.
Place balls of dough on nuts and flatten with bottom of small glass.
Place cookies on baking sheet, nut side up.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Cool and frost with 1 cup powdered sugar, 1 tablespoon butter and juice of 1/2 lemon, creamed until smooth.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Mix ingredients. Roll into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet 2-inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cheesy taco chip dip
directions: Fry ground beef in a pan or in the microwave (5 minutes). Drain.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Warm until melted together.
Put in crock-pot and serve with taco chips.

title: new england clam chowder with potatoes
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon; drain on paper towels.
Cook onion in bacon fat until tender. Stir in water, potatoes, celery, salt and pepper.
Cover; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cook for 15 minutes, until potatoes are tender.
Stir in clams with liquid.
Heat through.
Stir in milk; sprinkle with bacon.
Serves 4.

title: cloud puff cookies
directions: Warm eggs to room temperature and separate.
Whip egg whites, vanilla and vinegar in a bowl until white and frothy.
Keep whipping and add sugar a little at a time until stiff and glossy. Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheets and bake in preheated oven at 250° for about 1 hour or until cookies are light brown.
Let cookies cool.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: pop's chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a baking dish.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Top with mashed potatoes.

title: chicken pot pies
directions: Mix together and pour into a baking dish (large size).

title: pig licking cake
directions: Mix together.
Pour into two 9-inch cake pans (greased and floured).
Bake at 350°.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put apples in greased dish and sprinkle with lemon juice. Combine the rest of the ingredients and add melted butter; mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sad cake
directions: Beat eggs and stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Cook lasagna noodles.
Mix sauces and water; simmer.
Mix hamburger with sauces.
In casserole dish, put a layer of sauce, layer of noodles and 2 cups of cheese.
Add another layer of sauce, noodles and 2 cups of cheese.
Finish with layer of sauce.
Cook at 350° for 35 minutes until bubbly.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Blend cake mix with 2 eggs and melted butter.
Pour into an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Combine cream cheese, 2 eggs, vanilla and powdered sugar (minus 2 tablespoons).
Mix well and pour over batter in dish.
Bake 15 minutes at 325°.
Remove cake and sprinkle with 2 tablespoons sugar.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes longer.

title: apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Make pastry.
Mix the sugar, flour, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add salt.
Stir in apples.
Put in crust. Cover with top crust.
Seal and flute.
Put slits on top of crust. Put 3-inch strips of foil around edges of crust.
Remove foil during last 15 minutes of baking.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.

title: crustless quiche(microwave)
directions: Sprinkle cheese, bacon and onion in a 9-inch glass pie plate, ungreased.
Beat remaining ingredients together and pour over entire bacon mixture.
Bake in radar oven 9 minutes.
Turn dish 1/4 turn every 3 minutes of cooking time.
Let stand 10 minutes for center to set before cutting.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to directions.
Mix in 2 raw eggs.
Place in bottom of "Pammed" casserole dish.
Cook ground beef, adding all spices.
Drain and layer on top of macaroni.
Sprinkle with cheese and cover with sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Save 1/4 cup walnuts to roll cheese ball in. Soften cream cheese at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients in a bowl. Spread remaining walnuts on wax paper. Roll cheese ball in nuts.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cover with bread crumbs.
Dot with some butter and cook until golden brown at 350°.

title: white rice
directions: In wide frying pan, place rice, oil, garlic and onion.
Slowly brown rice over low heat, stirring constantly.
When rice is wheat colored, pour off most of oil.
Leave about 1 teaspoon and remove garlic.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in water and pour over rice. Simmer covered until liquid is absorbed (about 20 minutes).
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: boeuf or lamb bourguignon
directions: Cook salt pork; leave fat in skillet.
Add beef, salt and pepper; brown for 10 minutes.
Add garlic, onions and mushrooms. Sprinkle with flour and stir to coat evenly.
Add wine (salt pork), cloves, allspice, bay leaf, thyme and parsley.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender. Remove bay leaf, parsley and any fat on top.

title: potato rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2 tablespoons lukewarm water.
Scald milk, sugar, salt and shortening in top of double boiler.
Mash potatoes until smooth.
Add scalded mixture and cold water.
Cool to lukewarm temperature.
Add yeast and 1 1/2 cups flour; beat.
Stir in remaining flour.
Knead on board and place in warm place for 1 1/2 hours. Shape into rolls; bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: stir-fry pork and rice
directions: Take 2 chops and cut them into chunks or strips.
Put 2 tablespoons oil in pan and heat.
Add vegetables to pan and stir-fry until soft.
Remove vegetables.
Place pork strips in oil. Add seasoning and stir-fry until well cooked.
Replace vegetables and serve over rice.
Soy sauce may be added according to your personal taste.

title: fake blood
directions: Mix all three ingredients together and store in a covered container.
This mixture will produce a deep red cover.
You can change the color by varying the amount of red and blue drops.
Be careful not to get any food coloring on yourself or your clothes.

title: jamaican jerk chicken
directions: Mince scallions, garlic and peppers and put in large bowl. Squeeze 3 tablespoons of juice from limes and add to bowl with allspice, oil, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Put chicken in bowl, turn to coat, and marinate for 30 minutes.
Heat broiler.
Put chicken on broiler pan, reserving marinade.
Broil the chicken 4 to 6-inches from the heat source basting it occasionally with reserve marinade until browned and cooked through, about 30 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Dice apples, break eggs over, and mix with fork.
Add sugar, nuts, cinnamon, and oil.
Sift salt, baking soda, and flour.
Add to mixture.
Grease and flour 9x12 oblong pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325 degrees.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking dish; add peas and carrots. Bring to a boil 2 cups chicken broth and 1 can chicken soup. Pour over chicken and vegetables.
Mix flour, pepper, salt, buttermilk and butter, then spoon over chicken.
Bake for 30 minutes at 425°.

title: butterscotch sauce
directions: Place sugar, butter, salt and corn syrup in heavy saucepan. Cook over very low heat, without stirring, until a soft ball forms when dripped into cold water.
Cool slighlty.
Stir in cream. Sauce will thicken as it stands.
Can thin with 1 or 2 tablespoons milk or cream if a thinner sauce is desired.

title: chicken teriyaki
directions: Place last four ingredients in a pan and bring to a boil. Place cup up chicken in sauce pan and boil chicken about 45 minutes.
Take out of sauce and serve on platter.
I like to use all wings or all legs.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour cherries in bottom of greased dish. Pour drained pineapple on top (do not stir). Sprinkle dry cake mix on top, then pour melted butter on top (do not stir). Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes until tender. Drain potatoes. Add celery and onion. Add milk and bring to a boil. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into 1-inch pieces.
This will take 2 months. Cook on outside grill for 1 month at 400°.
This will serve 4,000 people.
If more are expected, add 2 rabbits, but only if necessary, as most people do not care to find a hare in their stew.

title: sweet pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions.
Mix all ingredients and boil 20 minutes.
Pour into sterile jars and seal at once.
Fills about 10 pints.

title: party punch
directions: Combine water and sugar in saucepan or microwave.
Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; add juices and bananas.
Freeze firm.

title: tuna casserole
directions: In large saucepan, combine the soup, veggies, tuna and milk. Heat until warm.
In another large pan, fill with water almost to top.
Bring to boil.
Add noodles and cook until tender; rinse. In large baking dish, add 1 layer of noodles.
Pour approximately 1/2 of the tuna mixture on top.
Place cheese on top.
Add another layer of noodles, sauce and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° approximately 15 to 20 minutes.

title: beanie weanies
directions: Put pork and beans in a pot.
Slice wieners and put in pot. Cook until hot.
Enjoy!

title: kristen's krispy apple krisp
directions: Grease a 9 x 2 x 13-inch pan. Pour the sliced apples with juice into pan.
Empty spice cake mix on top of the apples. Slice butter or margarine into pats. Spread over cake mix. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
If you desire, top with chopped nuts. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with vanilla ice cream!

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: In a large pan, combine potatoes with enough water to cover. Bring to boil and cook, covered, for about 12 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Drain off water.

title: salami cones
directions: You will need 3 empty egg cartons.

title: "a pretty trifle"
directions: Cut cake into 1/2-inch cubes.
In a pretty (see through) glass bowl, place a layer of cake cubes.
Spread about 1 cup of pudding over cake, forming a thin layer.
Top with a few tablespoons of cherry pie filling (doesn't need to make a complete layer). Continue layering until ingredients are used.
Make final layer of whipped topping.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place 1/2 of rye bread cubes in bottom of pan.
Layer in order:
sour cream, onion, sauerkraut, corned beef and Mozzarella cheese.
Top with remaining bread cubes.
Drizzle melted margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: more(serves 15 to 20 people)
directions: Cook in large frying pan, beef, sausage and onions.
When browned, add all remaining ingredients, except noodles and cheese, and cook for 15 minutes.
Stir in the cooked and drained noodles.

title: german chocolate brownies
directions: Mix and bake cake-like brownies as directed on the box.
In a medium saucepan, combine sugar, evaporated milk, egg yolks and shortening.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla, coconut and pecans. Cool 15 minutes at room temperature.
Spread evenly over cool brownies.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill and serve.

title: frances maley's bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake in muffin tins for 20 to 25 minutes in a 350° oven.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: healthy zucchini bread
directions: Combine in mixing bowl the first 5 ingredients. Sift together the dry ingredients and add to zucchini mixture and stir until blended.
Pour into 2 greased 8-inch bread pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove from pans and cool on rack.

title: garlicky quick bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Sift flour, baking powder and salt into a large bowl.
Add garlic and cheese.
Combine well.

title: dry hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in a glass container.
Makes great hostess and/or Christmas gifts.

title: karen's oregon artichoke sauce
directions: In large skillet, drain marinade from artichoke hearts; coarsely
chop
artichokes	and
set aside.
In skillet, saute mushrooms
in
hot	marinade until tender.	Add artichokes and remaining
ingredients, except spaghetti and Parmesan, back to skillet.
Simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti and sprinkle with Parmesan before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: world's best cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream the oleo and sugars.
Add egg, oil and vanilla.
In separate bowl, mix dry ingredients.
Add to creamed ingredients (a cup at a time); mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Cook for 12 minutes at 325°.
Makes 90 to 100.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Rinse and scrub potatoes; pat dry.
Prick a few times with a fork.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour or until soft.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Have all ingredients cooked and ready to mix.
(Use a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan or dish.)
Mix rice, chicken, broccoli, salt and soup.
Put in baking dish.
Top with cheese, then crushed corn flakes.

title: chile rellenos casserole
directions: Roast, peel and seed chilies.
Layer them alternately with cheese in a deep buttered 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Beat eggs, salt, pepper and cumin together.
Pour mixture over chilies and cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift together 1 1/3 cups flour, baking soda and salt. Add cinnamon, cloves and allspice. Cream together shortening and sugar; add egg and beat well. Add flour mixture alternately with 1 cup applesauce, beginning with flour and ending with flour. Mix raisins and nuts with 2 teaspoons flour; fold into batter. Bake at 350° about 45 minutes in a 9 x 9 x 1 1/2-inch greased pan.

title: micro-good beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat diagonally across the grain into thin strips.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, microwave in butter for 3 minutes on High.
Add mushrooms and liquid to equal 1 cup; stir in soup mix. Heat to boiling.
Add steak sauce and garlic powder.
Cook on Medium for 3 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Serve on thin or broad egg noodles.

title: broccoli cheese chicken
directions: In skillet over medium heat in hot margarine, cook chicken for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup, water and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Add broccoli.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 10 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix milk and pudding mix.
Spoon over bottom of dish.
Put layer of wafers.
Cover with sliced bananas.
Layer again, ending with pudding.
Put wafers and bananas around edge.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: rhubarb-strawberry freezer jam
directions: Mix rhubarb and sugar and let stand overnight.
Bring to a boil in morning in large pot, stirring constantly.
Cook 4 minutes at a boil.
Remove from heat and add strawberry jello, stirring until dissolved.
Skim if necessary.
Pack in sterile jars and freeze.

title: chocolate yogurt cheese freeze
directions: Prepare Yogurt Cheese 24 hours ahead of time (recipe follows). Stir together sugar and cocoa in a small microwave-safe bowl. Stir in water. Microwave on High 45 seconds or until mixture boils. Cool slightly. Add vanilla and mint. Stir cocoa mixture into Yogurt Cheese. Fold in whipped topping. Spoon into 8-inch square pan. Cover with plastic wrap. Freeze 2 to 4 hours until firm. Serve. Scoop into individual dessert dishes.

title: bonbons
directions: Mix all together, except semi-sweet chocolate and paraffin wax. After mixing well, roll into balls about the size of a quarter. Melt together on low heat the chocolate and the wax.
Dip the balls into wax and chocolate.
May use toothpick to dip them in chocolate.
Also, you may need to put balls in freezer to keep firm enough to dip.
After dipping, put on waxed paper until cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, soup and sour cream.
Place in 9 x 13-inch buttered casserole.
Cover with crumbs; sprinkle with poppy seed. Then drizzle melted margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pinon nut candy
directions: Mix sugar, water, margarine and vinegar in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and heat until the temperature is between 234° and 240° on a candy thermometer.
Cool and beat in the nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto a buttered pan or oiled paper.
Allow to set.

title: cranberry-orange relish
directions: In crockery cooker, combine sugar, orange peel and juice; stir until sugar is nearly dissolved.
Stir in cranberries.
Cover; cook on low heat setting for 6 hours.
Mash berries.
Chill until served.
Makes 4 cups.
